INSERT INTO `tuko_articles` VALUES (1,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/politics/584693-tharaka-nithi-crowd-walks-kimani-ichungwah-rutos-tour-mt-kenya/','Tharaka Nithi: Crowd Walks Out on Kimani Ichung\'wah During Ruto\'s Tour in Mt. Kenya','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Don\'t miss out! Join Tuko.co.ke Sports News channel on WhatsApp now!\n\nFaith Chandianya, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over three years of experience covering politics and Current Affairs in Kenya\n\nTharaka Nithi: Kikuyu MP Kimani Ichung’wah’s troubles appear to be mounting after he faced yet another hostile reception from a crowd in the Mt. Kenya region.\n\nThe incident occurred on Friday, April 4, the fourth day of President William Ruto\'s visit to the central region.\n\nIchung’wah began speaking to the crowd that had turned out in large numbers to hear from the president in Gatunga, Tharaka Nithi.\n\nRead also\n\nJustin Muturi says William Ruto approached him to join Kenya Kwanza coalition in 2022\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nHowever, shortly after Ichung’wah began speaking, several residents started leaving the rally one by one.\n\nIt began when Ichung’wah remarked that he felt at home and considered himself a close friend of the people of Tharaka Nithi.\n\nIchung’wah remained committed to delivering his speech and continued addressing the crowd despite a significant number of people walking out of the rally.\n\nThe Tharaka Nithi incident is not the first time Ichung\'wah has faced a cold reception in the Mt. Kenya region.\n\nOn Thursday, April 3, Ichung\'wah was heckled by residents of Ol Kalou in Nyandarua county as soon as he started speaking.\n\nRead also\n\nMurang\'a: Blow to Gachagua as Maragua MP ditches his camp, declares support for Ruto\n\nAny attempt Ichung\'wah made to deliver his remarks was met with louder jeers from the irate crowd, who rejected his talking points.\n\nIchung\'wah grew tired of attempting to address the crowd, thanked them, and abruptly ended his prepared speech.\n\nThe incident occurred on the third day of President Ruto’s regional visit, coinciding with the launch of significant development projects, including the Last Mile electricity connectivity and affordable housing initiatives in Ol Kalou Town.\n\nIchung\'wah was not the only one facing challenges during Ruto\'s third day touring Mt. Kenya, as Nyandarua woman representative Faith Gitau was also met with boos.\n\nHowever, unlike Ichung\'wah, no amount of heckling stopped Gitau from delivering her message to the people of Ol Kalou.\n\nGitau remained composed and continued delivering her points, even as the booing grew louder.\n\nAt one point, the woman rep even reassured the head of state not to worry about the jeering from the residents, explaining that they sometimes react in that manner.\n\nProofreading by Mercy Nyambura, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nFaith Chandianya (CA editor) Faith Chandianya is a multi-media journalist and a Current Affairs Editor at TUKO.co.ke. In 2023, she graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Media Science from Moi University. She has over four years experience in digital journalism. Email: Faith.Chandianya@tuko.co.ke\n\nMercy Nyambura (Copyeditor)','News','2025-04-05 07:19:42','2025-04-05 07:19:42',NULL),(2,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/politics/584668-justin-muturi-william-ruto-approached-join-kenya-kwanza-coalition-2022/','Justin Muturi Says William Ruto Approached Him to Join Kenya Kwanza Coalition in 2022','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: You’re One Course Away from Transforming Your Life. Learn Copywriting and Turn Your Passion into Profit\n\nFaith Chandianya, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over three years of experience covering politics and Current Affairs in Kenya\n\nFormer Public Service Cabinet secretary Justin Muturi has clarified how he came to join President William Ruto’s Kenya Kwanza coalition.\n\nMuturi claimed that he did not initiate contact with the head of state ahead of the 2022 General Election.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nIn a statement posted on his social media pages, Muturi said President Ruto approached him and invited him to join his campaign team, likely as part of efforts to boost support in the Mt. Kenya region.\n\nRead also\n\nJustin Muturi says Ruto is unfit to be president, claims he\'s corrupt: \"Dangerous character\"\n\nHe said their decision to work together was founded on shared values at the time—trust and a mutual commitment to serve the country with integrity.\n\nMuturi’s recent comments come just days after he officially relinquished his role in the Public Service docket following his dismissal.\n\nThe former attorney general addressed the media to share his perspective on his dismissal, following President Ruto’s claims that he was removed due to absenteeism from Cabinet meetings and incompetence.\n\nIn response, Muturi dismissed Ruto’s claims, stating that he was removed from office for speaking out against abductions and extrajudicial killings under the Kenya Kwanza administration.\n\nRead also\n\nJustin Muturi discloses he initially turned down William Ruto\'s job offer as AG\n\nMuturi acknowledged missing several Cabinet meetings but maintained that he had informed the president each time in advance.\n\nHe added that he had written confidential letters to the president, urging that the issues of abductions and extrajudicial killings be addressed in Parliament, but said his concerns were ignored and went unanswered.\n\nThe former Cabinet secretary reiterated his commitment to continue speaking out against abductions and forced disappearances.\n\nIn a related development, Muturi raised concerns over the abrupt manner in which he was instructed to hand over the Public Service Ministry to the Prime Cabinet Secretary Musalia Mudavadi.\n\nMuturi stated that he received a letter on Friday, March 26, just two days after his dismissal, instructing him to hand over the office on the same day.\n\nHe, however, noted that no handover notes were prepared and expressed a desire for Musalia to have a record of the operations from the time he took charge of the Public Service Ministry until his departure.\n\nHe stated that due to this, he scheduled the handover ceremony to take place on Tuesday, April 1.\n\nProofreading by Mercy Nyambura, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nFaith Chandianya (CA editor) Faith Chandianya is a multi-media journalist and a Current Affairs Editor at TUKO.co.ke. In 2023, she graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Media Science from Moi University. She has over four years experience in digital journalism. Email: Faith.Chandianya@tuko.co.ke\n\nMercy Nyambura (Copyeditor)','News','2025-04-05 07:19:51','2025-04-05 07:19:51',NULL),(3,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/entertainment/celebrities/584528-karen-nyamu-responds-man-claiming-curves-helped-senatorial-job-ungekuwa-mama-mboga/','Karen Nyamu Responds to Man Claiming Her Curves Helped Her Get Senatorial Job: “Ungekuwa Mama Mboga”','2003-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: Don\'t let unemployment hold you back. Start your digital marketing journey today.\n\nNominated senator Karen Nyamu has responded after a fan appeared to demean her.\n\nNyamu has always been known to be a fun and youthful leader, which seems to have tainted her reputation a little.\n\nSome have seen her as a \'joker\' and not worthy of being a senator, despite working her way to the top and being an advocate of the High Court of Kenya.\n\nThe politician had to hit back at a fan who questioned her credibility as senator, as she accompanied President William Ruto on his Mt. Kenya tour.\n\nRead also\n\nKareh B discloses ex cheated on her with cousin in her house: \"In my bed\"\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nNyamu shared photos on her Instagram, showing her next to the head of state as he launched projects and held rallies to speak to his supporters.\n\nIn one of the posts, a fan called out Nyamu, claiming that if it were not for her curves and good looks, which include her dimples, she would have been a mama mbonga.\n\nNyamu replied to the bashing, saying if that is the case, then she has to thank her curves every night and day for making her who she is.\n\nNyamu\'s post also attracted other positive and negative views. Here are a few of the reactions:\n\nlvin_51426 said:\n\ndanny.calvin said:\n\nmuringe33 said:\n\nunonymous_12x said:\n\nRead also\n\nKaren Nyamu: Video of senator talking ill of Mt. Kenya ikrs netizens\n\nrahmahsopranoz said:\n\nsamuelihomba.kamau said:\n\nmarble_coins said:\n\nEarlier, TUKO.co.ke reported that Nyamu irked many after speaking ill of Mt. Kenya voters amid Ruto\'s tour to the area.\n\nWhile driving to Sagana with Gatundu North Member of Parliament Elijah Njoroge Kúrúria, Nyamu said that after touching the mountain, it was time to do more than just that.\n\nNjoroge reacted to the senator\'s gross gesture by notifying Nyamu that as a church elder, he would be banished by pastors who were watching.\n\nThe mother of three also revealed that she would vie for the Nairobi Woman Representative seat in 2027 and warned those who feel entitled to their vote that she does not need them.\n\nRead also\n\nKayole Residents Rough Up Pastors for Preaching That Jesus Was Black: \"Haiwezekani\"\n\nShe also noted how much she loves her role as nominated senator, saying she has a lot of free time and avoids a lot of stress.\n\nProofreading by Mercy Nyambura, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nVictor Otengo (Entertainment editor) Victor Otengo is the Special Projects Lead and Editor at TUKO.co.ke. He attended the Multimedia University of Kenya, where he studied for a Bachelor\'s Degree in Journalism and Mass Communication. He has seven years of experience in journalism and has previously worked as a writer at Standard Digital, reporter and sports pundit at Kwese TV (under African Insights). Email: victor.otengo@tuko.co.ke.\n\nMercy Nyambura (Copyeditor)','News','2025-04-05 07:20:00','2025-04-05 07:20:00',NULL),(4,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/entertainment/584699-female-football-fan-cries-stands-ulinzi-stars-loss-mnafikiria-tunaskia-aje/','Female Football Fan Cries in Stands after Ulinzi Stars\' Loss: “Mnafikiria Tunaskia Aje?”','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nA female football fan has shown just how much she loves her team and hates it when they face defeat.\n\nIn a video that has gone viral, the popular fan, Chemiati aka The Boss Lady, was spotted in tears in the stands after her favourite team Ulinzi Stars lost to Sofapaka in the Kenyan Premier League on Friday, April 4.\n\nThe frustrated Chemiati did not hold back from shouting at her team to show them just how much she was gutted towards the loss and how much she was hurting.\n\nRead also\n\nDJ Mo offers KSh 10k reward for help to find TikToker who accused him of being deadbeat\n\nThe lady said that every time she goes to watch the games, she leaves highly disappointed and wants the players to open up if they are facing any challenges.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nChemiati even asked for a paybill number so that the fans could fundraise money to buy players if that is the reason the team underperforms.\n\nShe added that as Ulinzi\'s number one fan, she was hurt and wondered if the leadership was also entertaining the poor football.\n\nDuring her rant, some of the other lady fans tried to console Chemiarti from ranting, asking her to stay calm, but she was not having it.\n\nRead also\n\nKareh B discloses ex cheated on her with cousin in her house: \"In my bed\"\n\nHere are some of the reactions from the clip:\n\n@JosephChitechi4 said:\n\n@EEllect said:\n\n@davlgt76 said:\n\n@felixodero10 said:\n\n@BeingXam said:\n\n@task_ace said:\n\nIn another moment of frustration shared online, TUKO.co.ke reported just recently how irked Harambee Stars\' fans were when Raila Odinga\'s daughter Winnie showed up to Nyayo Stadium in an Arsenal jersey.\n\nRead also\n\nDJ Dibul celebrates fatherhood after welcoming first child: \"The sweetest thing\"\n\nWinnie was attending Kenya\'s World Cup qualifiers game against Gabon, which the home team lost in a dramatic encounter.\n\nFans online even claimed that Winnie had jinxed Harambee Stars leading to the loss.\n\nProofreading by Mercy Nyambura, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nVictor Otengo (Entertainment editor) Victor Otengo is the Special Projects Lead and Editor at TUKO.co.ke. He attended the Multimedia University of Kenya, where he studied for a Bachelor\'s Degree in Journalism and Mass Communication. He has seven years of experience in journalism and has previously worked as a writer at Standard Digital, reporter and sports pundit at Kwese TV (under African Insights). Email: victor.otengo@tuko.co.ke.\n\nMercy Nyambura (Copyeditor)','News','2025-04-05 07:20:09','2025-04-05 07:20:09',NULL),(5,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/kenya/584676-garissa-leader-warns-boda-boda-riders-carrying-women-lists-consequences/','Garissa Leader Warns Boda Boda Riders Against Carrying Women, Lists Consequences','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Don\'t miss out! Join Tuko.co.ke Sports News channel on WhatsApp now!\n\nA politician from Garissa is on the receiving end after warning women in the region against boarding boda bodas lest they face dire consequences.\n\nThe undated video showed the politician addressing a huge crowd where he asked them to be vigilant and punish women using boda bodas.\n\nOver the years, there have been several concerns from leaders and Muslim clerics in the North Eastern region who claimed boda bodas were not women-users friendly.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThe politician said:\n\nRead also\n\nLand Cruiser with notice about accepting gently used baby mamas cracks up Kenyans\n\nWatch the video below:\n\nHere are some of the reactions from social media users:\n\n@Asmaahani said:\n\n@امين said:\n\n@Joyce.k.nursecanada said:\n\n@Barethu said:\n\n@maestro said:\n\n@Ann Wanjiku said:\n\nRead also\n\nKaren Nyamu responds to man claiming her curves helped her get senatorial job: \"Ungekuwa mama mboga\"\n\n@sullo said:\n\nThe National Gender and Equality Commission (NGEC) reacted to Garissa politician\'s remarks, terming his statement as discriminatory.\n\nIn a statement on X, NGEC said:\n\nElsewhere, Mumias East Member of Parliament Peter Salasya recently banned Form Four leavers in his constituency from joining the boda boda business.\n\nAccording to the budding politician, he wants his ex-high schoolers to join a university or a tertiary institution where they can learn a skill.\n\nRead also\n\nBahati ignites debate after holding daughter while driving on highway: \"Endangering her life\"\n\nHe also said that further training also opens one\'s mind so that one can operate businesses with a new mentality that can help them grow financially.\n\nNetizens commended the leader for how he was thinking of the future of his constituents.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nAmondi Aroko (Entertainment editor) Amondi Aroko is an Entertainment Editor with seven years of experience in local and international media. She has worked at Family Media (Kenya), written for News Deeply, New York (USA) and done Africa news analysis on Arise News (Nigeria). Won the 2015 Local Heroes Journalism award by Deutsche Welle. Google News Initiative 2024 trainee and 2024 WAN-IFRA Media Leadership Accelerator Programme winner. Speaker at Code For Africa -media lab, and China trip attendee by CMG. Email: prisca.aroko@tuko.co.ke.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 07:20:19','2025-04-05 07:20:19',NULL),(6,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/politics/584720-nyeri-leaders-plead-locals-stop-heckling-ruto-concludes-mt-kenya-tour-hii-haisaidii/','Nyeri Leaders Plead with Locals to Stop Heckling as Ruto Concludes Mt Kenya Tour: \"Hii Haisaidii\"','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nDidacus Malowa, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over three years of experience covering politics and current affairs in Kenya.\n\nNyeri - Leaders have appealed for decorum ahead of President William Ruto\'s Mt Kenya tour stop in Nyeri county.\n\nAhead of his visit to Nyeri town and Othaya constituencies on Saturday, April 5, local leaders called for restraint, urging residents to stop heckling politicians during presidential events.\n\nRead also\n\nMutahi Kahiga says Ruto lost grip on Mt Kenya despite attending his Nyeri rally: \"Mlima una wenyewe\"\n\nThe appeal follows a series of confrontational incidents earlier in the week, where leaders allied to Kenya Kwanza were publicly shouted down by residents during Ruto’s stopovers in Nyandarua County.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nAddressing residents at separate forums, Nyeri governor Mutahi Kahiga cautioned against behaviour that he said could dent the region’s image and its standing in national development politics.\n\nKahiga, who has lately voiced concerns over the direction of Kenya Kwanza’s leadership, insisted that the presidency should be treated with dignity regardless of internal political rifts.\n\nThe call for calm comes in the wake of an embarrassing episode in Nyandarua county, where National Assembly Majority Leader Kimani Ichung’wah, Laikipia East MP Mwangi Kiunjuri and Woman Rep Faith Gitau were jeered by angry crowds, even as Ruto looked on.\n\nRead also\n\nKimani Ichung’wah heckled by angry crowd during William Ruto’s Mt. Kenya tour\n\nLeaders now fear that such scenes may play out again in Nyeri, further undermining the president’s message and casting a shadow over his tour.\n\nNyeri Town MP Duncan Mathenge called for what he described as political hygiene, warning that public disruptions during national events were unhelpful and counterproductive.\n\nOthaya MP Wambugu Wainaina, who will host the president in his constituency, urged constituents to give credit where it’s due, saying the head of state was only there to follow up on projects he had already initiated.\n\nRead also\n\nMutahi Kahiga speaks after attending William Ruto\'s rally in Nyeri: \"Don\'t read too much\"\n\nNyeri senator Wahome Wamatinga echoed similar sentiments, urging residents to separate politics from development.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nDidacus Malowa (Political and current affairs editor) Didacus Malowa is a political and current affairs editor at TUKO.co.ke. He holds a Bachelor\'s Degree in Communication and Media Technology with IT from Maseno University in 2021. He has over two years of experience in digital journalism. Email: didacus.malowa@tuko.co.ke','News','2025-04-05 07:20:30','2025-04-05 07:20:30',NULL),(7,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/people/family/584715-busia-mum-desperately-appeals-justice-mku-son-dead-forest-shule-iajibike/','Busia Mum Desperately Appeals for Justice for MKU Son Found Dead in Forest: \"Shule Iwajibike\"','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: How to Start Earning with Copywriting in Just 7 Days – Even if You’re a Complete Beginner\n\nA family from Rumbiye village, Funyula constituency, Busia county, is struggling to come to terms with the loss of a loved one.\n\nFen Palmer Bwire was emotionally laid to rest in his home village after he was found dead under unclear circumstances.\n\nThe Mount Kenya University (MKU) student\'s body was found in the forest in a suspected murder incident.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThe 19-year-old was allegedly murdered as his lifeless body was discovered on Monday, March 10, as shared by X user Davis M. Tariq.\n\nPalmer\'s mother, Jerusah Bwire, talked with pain during her teenage son\'s burial while being comforted by her family members.\n\nRead also\n\nKakamega family seeks justice after kin is allegedly killed over KSh 50 change: \"Hakuwa na makosa\"\n\nThe grieving mum said she desired that her son\'s death would be a sacrifice and offering that other children would not have to go through.\n\nJerusah noted there were conflicting reports surrounding the death of her teen son as she asked for justice.\n\nRead also\n\nKisumu: Father of Ober Boys student killed in crash says school denied him chance to pick up son\n\nShe argued the school\'s administration turned a blind eye to the circumstances surrounding her son\'s death.\n\nA guest urged government officials, including the Member of County Assembly (MCA), to follow up on the matter and ensure justice was served.\n\nHe was convinced Palmer was murdered as he pleaded with the politician to ask relevant authorities to speed up investigations into the heartbreaking issue.\n\nA woman urged the church to pray for the young people in the wake of the increasing number of deaths in the country.\n\nIn another story, it was a sorrowful moment as another university student was found dead.\n\nRead also\n\nVihiga man returns from work to find wife allegedly killed their 2 kids: \"Hatukukosana\"\n\nJoseph Kinyua was a second-year mechanical engineering student at the Dedan Kimathi University of Science and Technology in Nyeri county.\n\nHis body was retrieved from the Embassy Dam, and the sight shattered the hearts of many.\n\nKinyua was mourned by his former high schoolmates and university mates as they penned emotional messages.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nJohn Green (Editor of parenting content) John Green is an editor of parenting content on the Human Interest Desk. He graduated with a degree in Bachelor of Journalism from the Multimedia University of Kenya (MMU). He has also received training from Google and WAN-IFRA. He previously worked at The Exchange and SportsLeo. John joined Tuko.co.ke in 2022. Email: john.green@tuko.co.ke\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 07:20:40','2025-04-05 07:20:40',NULL),(8,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/entertainment/celebrities/584724-georgina-njenga-recalls-provider-2-relationships-bar/','Georgina Njenga Recalls Being Provider in 2 Relationships: “Bar Was Low”','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: You’re One Course Away from Transforming Your Life. Learn Copywriting and Turn Your Passion into Profit\n\nContent creator Georgina Njenga has opened up on providing for her previous lovers.\n\nGeorgina via her Instagram stories jumped on the bar was too low challenge recalling how she provided for two of her exes.\n\nThe mother of one said that she was done providing for grown-up men and did not understand why she allowed herself to.\n\nShe gave herself grace saying that she was growing and learning. Georgina said:\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nRead also\n\nKareh B discloses ex cheated on her with cousin in her house: \"In my bed\"\n\nGeorgina in 2023, claimed that she was the one paying all the bills while living with her ex Tyler Mbaya aka Baha.\n\nThis is after Nurse Judy exposed the child actor for borrowing money from her and failing to give it back under the guise that he was providing for his family.\n\nGeorgina in a leaked conversation with the US-based nurse revealed that the father of her child was battling gambling addiction.\n\nShe noted that she was the one paying all their bills leaving Kenyans dumbfounded on social media.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nPatricia Tonui (Entertainment editor) Patricia Tonui is a journalist and an entertainment editor at TUKO.co.ke. She was a Broadcast Journalism student at The University of Nairobi class of 2022 and has a 2-year experience working in digital media having previously worked at mpasho.co.ke. Patricia joined Tuko.co.ke in 2022. Reach out to patricia.tunoi@tuko.co.ke if you have entertaining, and informative news to share.','News','2025-04-05 07:21:00','2025-04-05 07:21:00',NULL),(9,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/politics/583183-raila-odingas-supporters-claim-peter-salasya-attacked-by-gabon-fans/','Raila Odinga\'s Supporters Claim Peter Salasya Was Attacked by Gabon Fans','2024-03-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nTUKO.co.ke journalist Ivan Mboto has over three years of experience reporting on politics and current affairs in Kenya\n\nNairobi – A section of Raila Odinga’s supporters has distanced itself from the attack on Mumias East Member of Parliament (MP) Peter Salasya, which occurred at Nyayo Stadium on Sunday, March 23.\n\nThe group, speaking at a Bunge la Wananchi discussion in Jacaranda, dismissed allegations that Raila’s followers were responsible for the violent incident that saw the youthful lawmaker roughed up and sent away by rowdy individuals.\n\nOmosh One Hour, a vocal political commentator at the gathering, clarified that the incident should not be politicised or used to create divisions along ethnic lines. He insisted that Salasya’s assault was perpetrated by fans from Gabon who had attended the sporting event at Nyayo Stadium, and not by Raila’s supporters from Luo Nyanza.\n\nRead also\n\nPeter Salasya speaks after being attacked at Harambee Stars game: \"Wameninyorosha\"\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThe discussion gained momentum as other speakers including Nuru Okanga weighed in on the matter.\n\nOkanga cautioned that the attack on Salasya could set a dangerous precedent, warning that such political tensions could escalate into retaliatory confrontations in Western Kenya.\n\nHe further urged young people to refrain from attacking politicians, reminding them that most lawmakers are legally armed and have security details that could respond aggressively if provoked.\n\nRead also\n\nMusalia Mudavadi condemns Peter Salasya’s attack at Nyayo Stadium: \"Respect must be given\"\n\nVideos seen by TUKO.co.ke showed Salasya arriving at the stadium for the 2026 FIFA World Cup qualifier match between Kenya’s Harambee Stars and Gabon, moments before being roughed up by a section of the crowd.\n\nSome assailants threw objects, including a trash bin, at the lawmaker, with his security team and police eventually escorting him to safety outside the stadium.\n\nThe apparent trigger for the attack was Salasya’s outspoken criticism of prominent political figures, notably ODM leader Raila and President William Ruto.\n\nChants of “Heshimu Raila (Respect Raila)” and “Respect the President” were heard from the assailants, suggesting the assault was politically motivated.\n\nRead also\n\nPeter Salasya: Mumias East MP Attacked During Kenya vs Gabon Game at Nyayo Stadium\n\nSalasya, a known critic of both leaders, had previously labelled Raila a “political conman” and clashed with his supporters, which may have fueled the hostility directed at him during the match.\n\nThe MP has vowed to continue criticising the ODM boss despite the attack meted out on him at Nyayo during the football match that was also attended by Raila.\n\nThrough his social media pages, the outspoken politician said he is not a coward, adding that threats by his tormentors won\'t silence him.\n\nPrime Cabinet Secretary Musalia Mudavadi condemned the assault on Salasya, calling it an act of political intolerance that threatens democracy.\n\nHe stressed that differing opinions should never lead to violence, urging leaders and citizens to embrace dialogue and mutual respect.\n\nRead also\n\nUganda: 2 Kenyan politicians among 4 killed in Tapaach Road crash\n\nMudavadi reminded Kenyans that respect must be both given and earned, warning that continued hostility could undermine national unity.\n\nMasolo Mabonga, HOD Current Affairs and Politics updated this article with details on Peter Salasya\'s reactions to the attacks at Nyayo stadium.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nHarry Ivan Mboto (Current affairs editor) Harry Ivan Mboto is an accredited journalist with the Media Council of Kenya (MCK) and a Current Affairs and Politics Editor at TUKO. He is a Linguistics, Media, and Communication student at Moi University and has over three years of experience in digital journalism. Have a news tip, query, or feedback? Reach him at: harry.ivan@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 07:21:21','2025-04-05 07:21:21',NULL),(10,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/politics/584134-william-ruto-claims-rigathi-gachagua-demanded-ksh-10b-i-ill/','William Ruto Claims Rigathi Gachagua Demanded KSh 10b: “I Said I’ll Not Do It”','2001-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nDidacus Malowa, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over three years of experience covering politics and current affairs in Kenya.\n\nNyeri - President William Ruto has opened up about his rift with former deputy president Rigathi Gachagua.\n\nHe alleged that his estranged deputy demanded KSh 10 billion in exchange for securing political support in the vote-rich Mt Kenya region.\n\nRead also\n\nWilliam Ruto showers Ndindi Nyoro with praises, explains why he was replaced: \"Fine gentleman\"\n\nDuring a joint media interview at Sagana State Lodge ahead of his weeklong tour of the region, Ruto claimed that Gachagua went as far as threatening to make him a one-term president if he failed to comply with the demand.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThe head of state disclosed that he was taken aback by Gachagua’s ultimatum but remained firm in his refusal to succumb to political blackmail.\n\nRuto made it clear that he rejected the demand outright, choosing to put his faith in the people of Kenya rather than political maneuvering.\n\nRead also\n\nWilliam Ruto names leaders Gachagua clashed with before impeachment: \"Kila siku ilikuwa kesi\"\n\nThe head of state further revealed that after securing the presidency, the rift with Gachagua started, with a series of public and private disputes following the election.\n\nHe described how, almost immediately after taking office, battles emerged involving some of his close allies and key figures in his administration.\n\nThe president further criticised Gachagua’s alleged involvement in these tensions, particularly his conflicts with key political figures and MPs.\n\nRead also\n\nRigathi Gachagua fires back at Ruto after tell-all interview: “Lying without blinking”\n\nRuto also shared his frustration over Gachagua\'s strained relationship with members of Parliament, noting that it had begun to spill into public view.\n\nIn a separate report, Ruto commended Kiharu MP Ndindi Nyoro, describing him as a capable leader.\n\nThe remarks came during the roundtable interview where Ruto emphasised the importance of youthful leadership.\n\nProofreading by Mercy Nyambura, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nDidacus Malowa (Political and current affairs editor) Didacus Malowa is a political and current affairs editor at TUKO.co.ke. He holds a Bachelor\'s Degree in Communication and Media Technology with IT from Maseno University in 2021. He has over two years of experience in digital journalism. Email: didacus.malowa@tuko.co.ke\n\nMercy Nyambura (Copyeditor)','News','2025-04-05 07:21:31','2025-04-05 07:21:31',NULL),(11,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/business-economy/584689-nations-divided-decisive-week-shipping-emissions/','Nations divided ahead of decisive week for shipping emissions','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: How to Start Earning with Copywriting in Just 7 Days – Even if You’re a Complete Beginner\n\nMembers of the International Maritime Organization (IMO) are divided over whether to approve a carbon tax on international shipping, ahead of a meeting starting on Monday to finalise emissions-reduction measures.\n\nThe carbon tax, the most ambitious measure on the table, would make it more expensive for shipping companies to emit greenhouse gases, encouraging them to curtail emissions.\n\nBut some member states, including China and Brazil, are proposing other measures, arguing the carbon levy would increase the cost of goods and contribute to food insecurity.\n\nThe IMO expects to come to an initial agreement by Friday next week on which mechanism to adopt to help reach carbon neutrality in shipping by 2050.\n\nThe stakes are high as shipping accounts for nearly three percent of global greenhouse gas emissions, according to the IMO.\n\n\"(It is) difficult to say what will happen next week,\" Fanny Pointet, sustainable shipping manager at European advocacy group, Transport and Environment, told AFP.\n\nRead also\n\nTaiwan earmarks $2.7 bn to help industries hit by US tariffs\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThe United States has been notably quiet about the issue, having not commented since President Donald Trump returned to the White House.\n\nThe Pacific and Caribbean island states are leading the group pushing for a carbon tax, with support from other countries including the UK.\n\nThey argue that funds raised from a levy could be redistributed to nations most vulnerable to climate change to help adapt and mitigate its effects.\n\n\"Climate change is a terrifying lived reality for my country,\" said Albon Ishoda, the Marshall Islands\' representative to the IMO.\n\nHowever, around 15 countries strongly oppose the carbon levy, arguing it would exacerbate inequalities between nations and raise the costs of goods such as palm oil, cereals and corn.\n\nConcerns are also mounting that the European Union, once a supporter of a carbon tax, could water down the measure in favour of a carbon credit system.\n\nRead also\n\nTrump tariffs to test resiliency of US consumers\n\nSuch a system would allow companies or countries to buy and sell credits representing the right to emit a certain amount of carbon dioxide.\n\nAccording to University College London research, the option of no levy presents the biggest risk to meeting the shipping sector\'s climate goals.\n\nIt could also distort fuel prices and create an uneven playing field, favouring states with strong industrial polices, such as China, researchers said.\n\n\"The fastest and cheapest energy transition is brought about by a strong levy,\" combined with a global fuel standard to reduce the carbon intensity of fuels used by ships, they added.\n\nChallenges also remain with the fuel standard system, particularly the risk of using alternative fuels such as palm oil and soybean oil, which indirectly contribute to emissions through deforestation, Pointet explained.\n\nWhile Brazil defends the key role of these biofuels, more than 60 environmental protection NGOs have raised objections to their inclusion in the future shipping fuel mix.\n\nOther potential solutions include synthetic hydrogen-based fuels, currently very expensive to produce, or the installation of wind-powered propulsion systems onboard ship.\n\nSource: AFP\n\nAFP AFP text, photo, graphic, audio or video material shall not be published, broadcast, rewritten for broadcast or publication or redistributed directly or indirectly in any medium. AFP news material may not be stored in whole or in part in a computer or otherwise except for personal and non-commercial use. AFP will not be held liable for any delays, inaccuracies, errors or omissions in any AFP news material or in transmission or delivery of all or any part thereof or for any damages whatsoever. As a newswire service, AFP does not obtain releases from subjects, individuals, groups or entities contained in its photographs, videos, graphics or quoted in its texts. Further, no clearance is obtained from the owners of any trademarks or copyrighted materials whose marks and materials are included in AFP material. Therefore you will be solely responsible for obtaining any and all necessary releases from whatever individuals and/or entities necessary for any uses of AFP material.','News','2025-04-05 07:21:40','2025-04-05 07:21:40',NULL),(12,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/people/family/584695-nairobi-mum-verge-abandoning-kid-by-roadside-rescued-by-wellwisher-depression-evident/','Nairobi Mum on Verge of Abandoning Kid by Roadside Rescued by Well-Wisher: \"Depression Is Evident\"','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nA kindhearted woman from Nairobi county has shown up at the nick of time to save a woman and her young child.\n\nAchieng\' Otieno took to social media to share her encounter and her decision to help the stranded family.\n\nOtieno noted she was on her way to work when her attention was captured by a crowd that surrounded the wo