tor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 07:21:49','2025-04-05 07:21:49',NULL),(13,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/entertainment/celebrities/584726-bradley-marongo-feature-bollywood-movie-naenda-india/','Bradley Marongo Says He Will Feature in Bollywood Movie: \"Naenda India”','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: How to Start Earning with Copywriting in Just 7 Days – Even if You’re a Complete Beginner\n\nBradley Marongo has unveiled the plans he has to make his brand international.\n\nThe influencer appeared on The Trend Show on Friday, April 4, where Amina asked him about his rise to stardom.\n\nBradley said he was of average height until he got to Class Seven.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nHe worked in the matatu industry for a while before his breakthrough.\n\nThe influencer admitted that he was initially tense when people would stop and stare at him, but he is now used to the attention.\n\nRead also\n\nBradley Marongo confesses his crush on Amina Abdi, gifts her iPhone live on TV\n\nBradley admitted that his life had changed for the better since becoming famous.\n\nAccording to Bradley, it was hard for him to get fitting clothes in Kenya, but that is a bygone.\n\nBradley addressed Kenyans being unimpressed with his content in Dubai, with some saying it was demeaning.\n\nThe influencer then said he was getting support from both local and international brands, and shared his plans.\n\nRead also\n\nKamene Goro says being celebrity stops her from going to supermarket: \"Get overwhelmed\"\n\nBradley dislosed that he has two managers and is looking for a personal assistant.\n\nKenyans wished him well, while others cautioned him against sharing his plans.\n\nJeddy Njuguna:\n\nEuriter Nyabs:\n\nTrazie Martins:\n\nMalach Ochengo Orina:\n\nMercy N. Toywa