d on her with cousin in her house: \"In my bed\"\n\nShe was released on KSh 5 million bond even as the investigation into the matter that gained national attention continues.\n\nHowever while going live on her new TikTok page Rish noted how her close friends ditched her when she got in the legal trouble.\n\nShe also noted how her phone could not stop ringing forcing her to divert all her calls to different phones.\n\nRead also\n\nSorrow as Kiambu college girl who went missing while going shopping is found dead\n\nRish also vowed to give her side of the story when the matter in court gets settled as she was barred from speaking about it now.\n\nShe was with her friend on TikTok who also encouraged Kenyans to consider the \'favour\' that Rish had now that her business was on the spot.\n\nHere is a video of Rish:\n\nElsewhere, a Kenyan man disclosed that his grandmother sold all her cows so they could afford to raise the fee to get jobs Rish announced.\n\nJohn Munju wanted to go work in Canada when he reached out to Rish and she offered to help him.\n\nHe did everything that was needed and paid the amount she wanted only for her to go radio silent on him.\n\nAfter months, he decided to return to Rish\'s office where he was told that he never managed to secure the Canadian visa.\n\nJohn was among the many Kenyans who came forward to share their experiences after trying to travel abroad for better opportunities.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nAmondi Aroko (Entertainment editor) Amondi Aroko is an Entertainment Editor with seven years of experience in local and international media. She has worked at Family Media (Kenya), written for News Deeply, New York (USA) and done Africa news analysis on Arise News (Nigeria). Won the 2015 Local Heroes Journalism award by Deutsche Welle. Google News Initiative 2024 trainee and 2024 WAN-IFRA Media Leadership Accelerator Programme winner. Speaker at Code For Africa -media lab, and China trip attendee by CMG. Email: prisca.aroko@tuko.co.ke.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 07:23:33','2025-04-05 07:23:33',NULL),(20,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/sports/556539-samantha-irvins-net-worth-earnings-a-wwe-announcer/','Samantha Irvin\'s net worth and earnings as a WWE announcer','2007-08-24 00:00:00','Tuko','Samantha Irvin’s net worth interests fans because of her dynamic career in music and acting, as well as her current role as a WWE ring announcer. Additionally, Samantha might be profiting from brand endorsement deals and partnerships, leaving fans wondering about the total extent of her wealth.\n\nFormer WWE wrestler Mark Henry introduced Samantha Irvin to the industry. At first, she attended a trial to become a wrestler but failed. During that period, she voiced some shows and was hired as a ring announcer, initially working at 205 Live and NXT before taking over Smackdown. Her quick rise attests to her skill and adaptability but also sparks curiosity about her pay. So, what is the WWE ring announcer\'s salary?\n\nRead also\n\nWho is Polly Brindle\'s ex-husband who cheated on her with two escorts?\n\nAs of 2024, Samantha\'s net worth is around $1 million. While her primary source of income is her WWE announcing role, she has engaged in other activities before, like music and acting.\n\nFor example, in 2016, she released her debut EP 27Underground, which is on SoundCloud along with other songs, but it is unclear if she earns from this. In addition, Samantha performed the American national anthem at various sports events, but it is not known if she is paid for these live performances.\n\nFurthermore, she appeared in shows such as Got 2B Trill: The Untold Story (2015), Got 2B Real (2012) and Social Girl (2018).\n\nBeyond these roles, Samantha has a huge social media following, with over 1 million Instagram followers and over 300,000 X fans, which allows her to boost her income through brand collaborations.\n\nRead also\n\nAshley Graham\'s weight loss: Here everything you need to know\n\nCompared to former WWE female announcers, Samantha is well-paid. While Alicia Taylor and Jojo Offerman earned $15,000 and $100,000, respectively, Samantha Irvin\'s salary from WWE is estimated to be $350,000 annually. Additionally, she makes $10,000 per fight and $20,000 pay-per-view per fight. Her compensation reflects her role as WWE\'s primary announcer.\n\nRead also\n\nDoes Marysol Patton\'s net worth make her the richest in RHOM?\n\nSamantha Irvin’s net worth of $1 million is a testament to her financial growth and success. Veteran presenters like Lillian Annette Garcia and Michael Buffer have praised her announcements. All in all, Samantha\'s rise has been nothing but inspiring, and if she keeps at it, she will make more accomplishments.\n\nTuko.co.ke also shared an article, is ballet a sport or an art? It is not considered a sport because of its lack of physical aggression. Ballerinas are seen as performers in the same way as singers and dancers. However, ballet carries both sporting and artistic elements. Find out why in the article.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nAgnes Amondi (Lifestyle and sports writer) Agnes Amondi is a journalist and sports content writer with 6 years of experience. Her sports writing journey began as an intern at Citizen Digital, Royal Media Services in Nairobi, Kenya. After graduating in 2019 with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Journalism from the United States International University-Africa (USIU-Africa), she wrote for several publications: soka25east.com, Her Football Hub, Tisini, and Spotcovery. At Tuko.co.ke, Agnes continues her sports writing endeavors by delivering insightful sports-related articles. Email: agnesamondi@gmail.com','News','2025-04-05 07:23:43','2025-04-05 07:23:43',NULL),(21,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/people/family/584664-mum-newborn-reportedly-switched-hospital-speaks-dna-results-sio-wangu/','Mum Whose Newborn Was Reportedly Switched in Hospital Speaks after DNA Results: \"Sio Wangu\"','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nA Tanzanian woman whose baby was allegedly switched in the hospital by a nurse is heartbroken by the DNA results.\n\nNeema Kirugala claimed her newborn was exchanged after she gave birth through caesarean section.\n\nKirugala had welcomed a bundle of joy at Mount Meru Regional Referral Hospital, but claimed her baby was swapped with another who died days later.\n\nShe challenged the medical facility as she asked for DNA tests to confirm if truly she was given was truly hers.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nNeema and her family were shattered and in denial as the tests confirmed the baby who died was hers.\n\nRead also\n\nDJ Mo offers KSh 10k reward for help to find TikToker who accused him of being deadbeat\n\nNeema\'s family member stood with her kin, refuting the DNA results that showed the baby who died was 99.9% Neema\'s.\n\nShe refused to accept the results as she bitterly wept, leaning on another family member\'s chest while asking about the updates.\n\nGeorge Onyango Daniel, a government official, urged the family to accept the results or take the matter to court and open a case if they were dissatisfied.\n\nRead also\n\nSylvia Kemunto: Sorrow as Multimedia University First Year student who went missing on Sunday is found dead\n\nHe claimed the due process had been followed and there was no foul play in the DNA testing.\n\nSeveral social media users sympathised with the grieving and hurting family as they shared their comments.\n\nelizabethismile6827:\n\nLameck-f5i:\n\nSaniaIdrisa-y7v:\n\nClaraGurti\n\nRead also\n\nWoman whose baby was allegedly changed in hospital relieved as nurse is dismissed\n\nestermpare4078:\n\nIn another story, Kirugala was relieved after the nurse who allegedly swapped her baby was arrested and relieved.\n\nThe nurse had reportedly brought another child in a strange shawl, stating he was Neema\'s, but the mum refused.\n\nNeema said the baby looked pale and had medical conditions, which made her question the nurse.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nJohn Green (Editor of parenting content) John Green is an editor of parenting content on the Human Interest Desk. He graduated with a degree in Bachelor of Journalism from the Multimedia University of Kenya (MMU). He has also received training from Google and WAN-IFRA. He previously worked at The Exchange and SportsLeo. John joined Tuko.co.ke in 2022. Email: john.green@tuko.co.ke\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 07:23:53','2025-04-05 07:23:53',NULL),(22,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/entertainment/celebrities/584666-kamene-goro-celebrity-stops-supermarket-overwhelmed/','Kamene Goro Says Being Celebrity Stops Her from Going to Supermarket: \"Get Overwhelmed\"','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nKamene Goro has admitted that her life has changed because of fame.\n\nThe media personality has made a name for herself through radio, and also hosts events at nightclubs.\n\nAccording to Kamene, she cannot do some activities she previously enjoyed before becoming famous.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nKamene explained her decision, noting that some people infringe on her personal space.\n\nRead also\n\nFemale football fan cries in stands after Ulinzi Stars\' loss: \"Mnafikiria tunaskia aje?\"\n\nShe noted that she is a different person away from the limelight.\n\nHowever, some Kenyans said that they cared less when they met celebrities in person:\n\nAshahaolo:\n\nshix_mish:\n\nruth_caster91:\n\nRead also\n\n\"I did all the work but colleague took all the credit, what should I do?\": Expert advises\n\nItselizabethtanzania:\n\nchristopherg266:\n\nheatherrayy_21:\n\nSlowbunde:\n\nMisscwk:\n\nlee.worldwide:\n\nItsevemuturi:\n\nKamene previously lamented that women were too available to men nowadays.\n\nShe said that a while back, men had to sweat before getting a woman’s attention and urged women to have pride.\n\nKamene said that women should be selfish with their time and set high standards and adhere to them. For instance, Kamene said that she does not pick up calls past 8pm.\n\nRead also\n\nPastor Ng\'ang\'a tells off woman lamenting about hubby leaving her: \"Ni hii nywele”\n\nKamene values her privacy, and previously told Kenyans to stop poking noses in her blissful marriage with DJ Bonez.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nWilliam Osoro (Entertainment editor) William Osoro is a TUKO.co.ke entertainment and senior special formats editor with over six years of experience in digital & print media. Osoro started his career at the Standard Media Group as a sub-editor before joining TUKO. Osoro won the Innovation Award at the Standard Group in 2018 and was quadruply recognised for his stellar performance at TUKO. He had the most read article in the whole of 2022. He holds a Bachelor’s Degree in Media Science from Moi University. Email: william.osoro@tuko.co.ke.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 07:24:02','2025-04-05 07:24:02',NULL),(23,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/sports/569235-who-charles-leclercs-girlfriend-meet-alexandra-saint-mleux/','Who is Charles Leclerc\'s girlfriend? Meet Alexandra Saint Mleux','2009-12-24 00:00:00','Tuko','Charles Leclerc is not a new name to Formula 1 racing fans. Since his debut in 2018, Leclerc has consistently demonstrated his prowess on the track, securing multiple Grand Prix victories. Off the track, his girlfriend, Alexandra Saint Mleux, has become a familiar face in the F1 community, known for her elegance and support. But aside from the relationship, what else do you know about Charles Leclerc\'s girlfriend?\n\nCharles Leclerc\'s girlfriend has captured the attention of fans worldwide. Her numerous public appearances at races and events have made her popular among Formula 1 racing fans. Her support for Charles, whether cheering from the stands or sharing moments on social media, has endeared her to many.\n\nRead also\n\nWho is Madelyn Cline dating after Pete Davidson and Chase Stoke relationships?\n\nCharles Leclerc\'s girlfriend is Alexandra Malena Saint Mleux, a popular internet personality and art lover. Where is Alexandra Saint Mleux from? She is from France and has lived in Monaco and Paris. Saint Mleux was born in Cancun, Mexico, but reportedly owns an Italian passport. She revealed her birthplace during the 2023 Mexican Grand Prix.\n\nHow old is Alexandra Saint Mleux? The internet personality is 22 years old (as of 2024). She was born on June 19, 2002, and her zodiac sign is Gemini.\n\nShe has mixed ethnicity. Alexandra Saint Mleux\'s parents come from diverse backgrounds, with her father being French-Argentine and her mother being Mexican. Due to her varied heritage, Alexandra speaks four languages fluently: French, Italian, English, and Spanish.\n\nSaint Mleux attended the prestigious Ecole Du Louvre in Paris, France, from 2021 to 2024. She graduated with a Bachelor of Arts in general studies.\n\nRead also\n\nCentral Cee\'s ethnicity, nationality, parents, and religion\n\nAlexandra is a social media personality and art lover. She is popular on TikTok and Instagram, with millions of followers on each platform. Her content is mainly about fashion, travel, and lifestyle on her main TikTok and Instagram channels and art content on her secondary [Instagram] page.\n\nThe couple first raised dating speculation after fans noticed Alexandra in the background of a TikTok video of Charles during the Paris Fashion Week in March 2023. Many were curious whether they were dating, given that Charles had previously separated from his girlfriend of three years, Charlotte Sine, in December 2022.\n\nIn May 2023, the speculation grew after Alexandra attended the Monaco Grand Prix as an official guest with Charles Ferrari\'s team. Soon after, Leclerc appeared in an interview with Gala France, acknowledging being in a relationship. However, he never mentioned his mysterious girlfriend\'s name.\n\nRead also\n\nWho is Lola Tung\'s boyfriend amid Christopher Briney dating rumours?\n\nIn July 2023, Charles Leclerc and Alexandra appeared publicly at the Wimbledon Tennis Tournament, confirming the dating rumours. In August 2023, paparazzi pictured the couple vacationing in Sardinia, Italy.\n\nSince then, they have appeared together at various events and races, including the Las Vegas Grand Prix in November 2023. In May 2024, Saint Mleux attended the Miami Grand Prix and the Monaco Grand Prix, with Leclerc finishing third and first, respectively.\n\nRead also\n\nSheila Carrasco\'s fun facts and things you didn\'t know about her\n\nCharles Leclerc\'s relationship with his girlfriend, Alexandra Saint Mleux, has fascinated F1 fans since being spotted together in March 2023. Alexandra, a social media influencer and art lover, has quickly become a favourite among fans, often supporting Charles at his races.\n\nAre you looking for more information about Andrew Huberman\'s girlfriend? Tuko.co.ke published an informative article about the renowned neuroscientist\'s love life.\n\nAndrew Huberman is a renowned neuroscientist and tenured Stanford University School of Medicine professor. He is best known for his popular Huberman Lab podcast, which focuses on neuroscience, health, and science-related topics. But aside from his career, what else do you know about Andrew Huberman\'s relationship status?\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nSimon Ayub (Lifestyle writer) Simon Ayub is a Content Manager, Strategist, and writer who joined Tuko\'s team in 2019. He graduated in 2014 with a BSc in Agricultural Economics and is a CPA. Simon has over a decade of experience creating content for nyagah.co.ke, the Hoth and other platforms. He works on content encompassing biographies, fashion and lifestyle, gaming, and more. Simon was awarded the \"Writer of the Year\" 2024 on Tuko. In 2023, Simon finished the AFP course on Digital Investigation Techniques and, in 2024, expanded their skills through the Google Initiative Course. You can reach him via simonayub@gmail.com.','News','2025-04-05 07:24:13','2025-04-05 07:24:13',NULL),(24,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/business-economy/584698-tiktok-faces-deadline-ditch-chinese-owner/','TikTok faces new US deadline to ditch Chinese owner','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Don\'t miss out! Join Tuko.co.ke Sports News channel on WhatsApp now!\n\nTikTok on Friday was hours from a deadline to find a non-Chinese owner or face a ban in the United States.\n\nThe hugely popular video-sharing app, which has more than 170 million American users, is under threat from a US law that passed overwhelmingly last year and orders TikTok to split from its Chinese owner ByteDance or get shut down in the United States.\n\nUS President Donald Trump on Thursday said his administration was \"very close\" to a deal to find a buyer for TikTok, adding that it involved \"multiple\" investors but giving no further details.\n\nMotivated by national security fears and widespread belief in Washington that TikTok is ultimately controlled by the Chinese government, the law took effect on January 19, one day before Trump\'s inauguration.\n\nIn the hours before that deadline, TikTok temporarily shut down in the United States and disappeared from app stores, to the dismay of millions of users.\n\nRead also\n\nTrump goads China after Beijing retaliates in global trade war\n\nBut the Republican president quickly announced a 75-day delay and TikTok subsequently restored service to existing users, returning to the Apple and Google app stores in February.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThat delay is set to expire at midnight (0400 GMT) on April 5, but Trump has repeatedly downplayed risks that TikTok is in danger, saying he remains confident of finding a buyer for the app\'s US business.\n\nThe president also suggested TikTok could even be part of a broader deal with China to ease the stinging tariffs he imposed on Beijing as part of a worldwide blitz of levies.\n\nAsked Thursday if he was willing to make deals with countries on tariffs, he said: \"As long as they are giving us something that is good. For instance with TikTok.\"\n\n\"We have a situation with TikTok where China will probably say we\'ll approve a deal, but will you do something on the tariffs. The tariffs give us great power to negotiate,\" he added.\n\nRead also\n\nTikTok must find non-Chinese owner by Saturday to avert US ban\n\nAccording to reports, the most likely solution would see existing US investors in ByteDance roll over their stakes into a new independent global TikTok company.\n\nAdditional US investors, including Oracle and Blackstone, the private equity firm, would be brought on to reduce ByteDance\'s share.\n\nMuch of TikTok\'s US activity is already housed on Oracle servers, and the company\'s chairman, Larry Ellison, is a longtime Trump ally.\n\nBut uncertainty remains, particularly over what would happen to TikTok\'s valuable algorithm.\n\n\"TikTok without its algorithm is like Harry Potter without his wand — it\'s simply not as powerful,\" said Forrester Principal Analyst Kelsey Chickering.\n\n\"If the TikTok experience degrades, users, creators, and advertisers will spend more time and money on other media channels,\" she added.\n\nThe New York Times suggested the new company could license it from ByteDance.\n\nSuch an arrangement would go against the spirit of the law, which is in part based on the premise that TikTok\'s algorithm can be weaponized by the Chinese against US interests.\n\nRead also\n\nAsian stocks extend global rout after Trump\'s shock tariff blitz\n\nAmazon has also reportedly made a last-minute bid to buy TikTok.\n\nOther proposals include an initiative called \"The People\'s Bid for TikTok,\" launched by real estate and sports tycoon Frank McCourt\'s Project Liberty initiative.\n\nArtificial intelligence startup Perplexity recently expressed interest in buying TikTok, as did a joint venture involving YouTube mega-celebrity MrBeast and another bid from adult content platform OnlyFans.\n\nTrump, though he supported a ban in his first term, has lately become a TikTok defender, seeing it as a reason more young voters supported him in November\'s election.\n\nOne of his major political donors, billionaire Jeff Yass, is a major stakeholder in parent company ByteDance.\n\nSource: AFP\n\nAFP AFP text, photo, graphic, audio or video material shall not be published, broadcast, rewritten for broadcast or publication or redistributed directly or indirectly in any medium. AFP news material may not be stored in whole or in part in a computer or otherwise except for personal and non-commercial use. AFP will not be held liable for any delays, inaccuracies, errors or omissions in any AFP news material or in transmission or delivery of all or any part thereof or for any damages whatsoever. As a newswire service, AFP does not obtain releases from subjects, individuals, groups or entities contained in its photographs, videos, graphics or quoted in its texts. Further, no clearance is obtained from the owners of any trademarks or copyrighted materials whose marks and materials are included in AFP material. Therefore you will be solely responsible for obtaining any and all necessary releases from whatever individuals and/or entities necessary for any uses of AFP material.','News','2025-04-05 07:24:22','2025-04-05 07:24:22',NULL),(25,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/business-economy/584716-kenya-institute-mass-communication-announces-jobs-casuals-kcse-d/','Kenya Institute of Mass Communication Announces Jobs for Casuals: \"KCSE D-\"','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','PAY ATTENTION: Flexible Payment Plans Available! Invest in Yourself & See the Return with Our Affordable Copywriting Course!\n\nJaphet Ruto, an editor at TUKO.co.ke, brings over eight years of expertise in finance, business, and technology, providing valuable insights into economic trends both in Kenya and globally.\n\nThe Kenya Institute of Mass Communication (KIMC) has advertised 19 vacancies for casual workers.\n\nKIMC\'s vacant positions include jobs for cooks, cleaners, gardeners and housekeepers.\n\nIn an advert published on its website, the institution asked interested and suitable candidates to submit their applications by Friday, April 11.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThe state-owned institution said successful candidates will be offered three-month contracts.\n\nRead also\n\nKCB Bank announces several managerial job openings for Kenyans in April\n\nRequirements:\n\nRequirements:\n\nRequirements:\n\nRequirements:\n\nRequirements:\n\nRequirements:\n\nRead also\n\nMaseno, Kabianga universities advertise several jobs for Kenyans\n\nRequirements:\n\nKIMC director and chief executive officer (CEO) Peter Wakoli asked applicants to submit their CVs and certificates to his office.\n\nThe institution is located along Shikanga Road in Nairobi.\n\nIn other news, the Kisii county government declared 110 jobs for professionals in diverse fields.\n\nThe devolved unit requested that interested candidates submit their resumes by April 23 after announcing the open vacancies on social media.\n\nMedical officers, registered nurses, and registered clinical officers are among the available positions.\n\nRead also\n\nKUCCPS application 2025: University and TVET portal open for 2024 KCSE candidates\n\nElsewhere, the National Youth Service (NYS) advertised 50 jobs for its graduates in the UAE.\n\nThe African Population and Health Research Center (APHRC) also invited applications to fill 66 vacancies for field interviewers.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nJaphet Ruto (Current Affairs and Business Editor) Japhet Ruto is an award-winning TUKO.co.ke journalist with over eight years of working experience in the media industry. Ruto graduated from Moi University in 2015 with a Bachelor’s Degree in Communication and Journalism. He is a Business & Tech Editor. Ruto won the 2019 BAKE Awards’ Agriculture Blog of the Year. He was named TUKO.co.ke\'s best current affairs editor in 2020 and 2021. In 2022 and 2023, he was TUKO.co.ke\'s best business editor. He completed the Experimenting with new formats and Advance digital reporting curriculum from Google News Initiative. Email: japhet.ruto@tuko.co.ke.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 07:24:31','2025-04-05 07:24:31',NULL),(26,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/kenya/counties/584719-sylvia-kemunto-main-suspect-students-murder-surrenders-police-revisit-crime-scene-clues/','Sylvia Kemunto: Main Suspect in Student\'s Murder Surrenders as Police Revisit Crime Scene for Clues','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nDidacus Malowa, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over three years of experience covering politics and current affairs in Kenya.\n\nThe main suspect in the tragic murder of Multimedia University student Sylvia Kemunto has turned himself in to the police.\n\nEric Mutinda, believed to have been involved in the brutal killing, surrendered to authorities at Sultan Hamud Police Station in Makueni county early on the morning of Friday, April 4.\n\nRead also\n\nBoaz Zachary: Chaos rock Maseno University as student is killed, body dumped\n\nMutinda, whose connection to the victim has been confirmed, is currently in police custody, where he is assisting detectives with the investigation.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nSources indicate that Eric Mutinda was romantically involved with Sylvia Kemunto, and that their relationship may have played a role in the tragic turn of events.\n\nReports indicate that it was after intense discussions with his parents that Mutinda chose to surrender to the authorities. They escorted him to the station, where he was promptly taken into custody.\n\nThis development follows the shocking discovery of Kemunto’s lifeless body, which was found stuffed inside a water tank atop a hostel at Multimedia University.\n\nThe incident, which occurred on Tuesday, April 1, has sent shockwaves across the country, as many continue to mourn the loss of the young woman.\n\nRead also\n\nRachealine Rutto: Murder suspect arrested in brutal killing of 45-year-old Bomet woman\n\nIn the wake of Mutinda’s surrender, homicide detectives returned to Multimedia University to retrace Kemunto’s final moments.\n\nThey meticulously combed through the crime scene in search of fresh evidence that could help clarify the details of the murder.\n\nAmong the items collected from the scene were Sylvia’s beddings and footwear, as well as items belonging to the suspect.\n\nThese pieces of evidence will undergo forensic testing as investigators piece together the timeline of the crime and its possible motives.\n\nIt is believed that on the day Sylvia went missing, Mutinda had entered her room at the university.\n\nInitially questioned by detectives on campus, Mutinda later vanished, prompting a manhunt by the police.\n\nRead also\n\nKenya newspapers review: Cracks emerge in Gachagua’s camp as allies disagree over his strategy\n\nNow in the custody of detectives from the Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI), Mutinda has been transferred to Nairobi for further questioning.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nDidacus Malowa (Political and current affairs editor) Didacus Malowa is a political and current affairs editor at TUKO.co.ke. He holds a Bachelor\'s Degree in Communication and Media Technology with IT from Maseno University in 2021. He has over two years of experience in digital journalism. Email: didacus.malowa@tuko.co.ke','News','2025-04-05 08:25:46','2025-04-05 08:25:46',NULL),(27,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/sports/football/584678-football-world-reacts-kevin-de-bruynes-manchester-city-exit-announcement/','Football World Reacts to Kevin De Bruyne’s Manchester City Exit Announcement','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: Don\'t let unemployment hold you back. Start your digital marketing journey today.\n\nKevin De Bruyne has announced that he will leave Manchester City at the end of the season and fans and players have paid their tributes.\n\nKevin De Bruyne has announced that he will leave Manchester City when the 2024/25 season concludes. The 33-year-old has shown signs of decline, exacerbated by injuries.\n\nThe Belgian won 16 trophies at the club, including six Premier League and the 2023 Champions League.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nHe joined the club in 2015 from Wolfsburg and went on to become one of the greatest midfielders in history.\n\nRead also\n\nChelsea boss Enzo Maresca makes bold claim about his player after beating Tottenham\n\nHe registered 106 goals and 174 assists in 413 appearances for the defending Premier League champions.\n\nHe led in assists in 2017/18, 2019/20 and 2022/23.\n\nHe has started 19 matches this season and his performances regressed.\n\nDe Bruyne was one of the foundations of Guardiola\'s team when he joined the club in 2016. Guardiola formed a devastating team with the Belgian alongside David Silva and Sergio Aguero.\n\nRead also\n\nArsenal star shares reason he mocked Haaland in Arsenal\'s win over Man City\n\n@ToniKroos:\n\n@SamLee:\n\n@InvertTheWing:\n\n@joethomlinson:\n\n@ArminCFC_:\n\nRiyad Mahrez, Aymeric Laporte, and Neymar also sent their best wishes.\n\nRead also\n\nBukayo Saka produces lovely celebration after scoring on Arsenal return\n\nTUKO.co.ke earlier reported that former Manchester United goalkeeper Ben Foster named his top Premier League midfielders.\n\nFoster picked Paul Scholes in the no.1 spot and put De Bruyne second, but sparked angry reactions.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nEdwin Kiplagat (Sports Editor) Edwin Kiplagat has 8 years of experience in journalism and is currently a sports editor at Tuko. He has written sports stories from across the African continent while at Africa InSight, ESPN, Editec, and Sports Brief. Edwin obtained a degree in Journalism from Multimedia University in 2016. Email: edwin.kiplagat@sportsbrief.com.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 08:25:56','2025-04-05 08:25:56',NULL),(28,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/business-economy/584727-aphrc-advertises-jobs-kenyan-diploma-holders-lists-requirements/','APHRC Advertises Jobs for Kenyan Diploma Holders, Lists Other Requirements','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','PAY ATTENTION: Flexible Payment Plans Available! Invest in Yourself & See the Return with Our Affordable Copywriting Course!\n\nJaphet Ruto, an editor at TUKO.co.ke, has over eight years of experience in finance, business, and technology, offering expert insights into economic trends in Kenya and around the world.\n\nThe African Population and Health Research Center (APHRC) has announced 23 vacancies for field interviewers.\n\nIn an advert published on its website, the research institution asked interested and qualified candidates to submit their academic and professional documents by Sunday, April 20.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThe organisation noted successful candidates will work under its research project titled “Reducing Delays in Cancer Care in Sub-Saharan Africa.\n\nRead also\n\nHustler Fund advertises CEO vacancy with April deadline\n\nRead also\n\nKisii county advertises 110 permanent jobs for nurses, other positions\n\nIn related news, the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication (KIMC) advertised jobs for casual workers.\n\nThe vacancies include cooks, housekeepers, gardeners and other positions.\n\nKisii county also announced 110 positions for professionals in various sectors. The devolved unit asked interested Kenyans to send their resumes by April 23.\n\nRead also\n\nEquity Bank Kenya advertises entry, middle-level and managerial jobs\n\nElsewhere, President William Ruto\'s administration unveiled a nationwide recruitment drive to hire skilled and semi-skilled workers in the Gulf.\n\nRuto promised to secure at least two million jobs for the youth abroad.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nJaphet Ruto (Current Affairs and Business Editor) Japhet Ruto is an award-winning TUKO.co.ke journalist with over eight years of working experience in the media industry. Ruto graduated from Moi University in 2015 with a Bachelor’s Degree in Communication and Journalism. He is a Business & Tech Editor. Ruto won the 2019 BAKE Awards’ Agriculture Blog of the Year. He was named TUKO.co.ke\'s best current affairs editor in 2020 and 2021. In 2022 and 2023, he was TUKO.co.ke\'s best business editor. He completed the Experimenting with new formats and Advance digital reporting curriculum from Google News Initiative. Email: japhet.ruto@tuko.co.ke.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 08:26:06','2025-04-05 08:26:06',NULL),(29,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/people/family/584620-slyvia-kemuntos-mum-tearfully-narrates-how-learnt-death/','Sylvia Kemunto’s Mum Tearfully Narrates How She Learnt of Her Death','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: How to Secure Copywriting Gigs Fast – So You Can Turn Words Into Money Right Now\n\nNairobi - The mother of Sylvia Kemunto, a First-Year student at Multimedia University (MMU), is in deep mourning following the tragic death of her daughter.\n\nSylvia went missing on Sunday, March 30, under mysterious circumstances, leaving her mother worried.\n\nShe had sent her money through a church elder’s phone, but the Mass Communication and Computer Science student did not respond to confirm whether she had received the cash.\n\nKnowing that was unlike her daughter, the worried mum tried calling her to confirm, but her calls went unanswered.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nRead also\n\nSylvia Kemunto: Sorrow as Multimedia University First Year student who went missing on Sunday is found dead\n\nConcerned for her daughter’s safety, the distraught woman went to MMU, only to find out that her daughter was missing.\n\nShe filed a missing person’s report at Lang’ata Police Station after the school management confirmed her daughter’s disappearance, prompting a frantic search.\n\nOn the fateful Sunday, Sylvia’s roommate left her doing laundry in the hostel and went to church.\n\nAccording to reports, her alleged boyfriend, also a First-Year student at the institution, visited Sylvia’s room at around 1pm on the same day she went missing.\n\nHe was later allegedly seen dragging Sylvia’s suitcase from her room to his within the school premises.\n\nHis roommate reportedly saw the suitcase in their room that evening but noticed it was missing the following morning.\n\nRead also\n\nKenyan woman desperately seeks help to find sister who went missing 18 years ago\n\nThe deceased student’s phone signal was last traced within the school compound, but the phone was switched off at around 10pm that Sunday.\n\nA foul smell from Sylvia’s hostel block prompted a search, leading to the discovery of her body inside a water tank on the rooftop of one of the hostels on Wednesday, April 2.\n\nInvestigators revealed that retrieving the young woman’s body took them three hours, as the tank had been sealed with wire and weighed down with a heavy stone.\n\nHer body was moved to the City Mortuary as the family awaits a post-mortem examination.\n\nRead also\n\nSorrow as Kiambu college girl who went missing while going shopping is found dead\n\nHer alleged boyfriend, who is in hiding, remains the main suspect as investigations into the murder continue.\n\nThe family is now seeking justice following her tragic death. Sylvia’s uncle, Clinton Nyamari, questioned how a student could be killed within the school premises without anyone noticing.\n\nSimilarly, Kenyans also joined them in demanding justice in the wake of rising femicides. Here are some of the comments:\n\nNjambi Wa Julie said:\n\nAntonate Mihegwa Okuso said:\n\nBŕìàñ Oñďìéķ said:\n\nIn other news, TUKO.co.ke reported that Bosibori Ratema broke down in tears while seeking justice for her deceased daughter, Phanice Kerubo.\n\nRead also\n\nKiambu man allegedly kills wife, flees after posting cryptic Facebook confession\n\nKerubo allegedly died while waiting to give birth at a hospital, as the nurses told her she was not yet ready despite hours of labour pains and a full day of waiting.\n\nBosibori wept bitterly, noting that Kerubo was her only child, and stated that the nurses and doctors at the facility could have prevented her death.\n\nRacheal Nyaguthie, HoD Human Interest, contributed to this article with details on the family demanding justice\n\nProofreading by Mercy Nyambura, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nLynn-Linzer Kibebe (Human interest editor) Lynn-Linzer Kibebe is a versatile and resolute digital journalist with more than five years of experience in media. She currently works as a human interest editor at TUKO.co.ke, where she focuses on feel-good stories and day-to-day pieces that touch on the human aspect of life driving societal change. She can be reached via email address lynn-linzer.kibebe@tuko.co.ke\n\nMercy Nyambura (Copyeditor)','News','2025-04-05 08:26:15','2025-04-05 08:26:15',NULL),(30,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/entertainment/584682-land-cruiser-notice-accepting-gently-baby-mamas-cracks-kenyans/','Land Cruiser With Notice About Accepting Gently Used Baby Mamas Cracks Up Kenyans','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: You’re One Course Away from Transforming Your Life. Learn Copywriting and Turn Your Passion into Profit\n\nA Kenyan motorist has made his car go viral after pasting a hilarious sticker on its back.\n\nAlways trust Kenyans to have the most hilarious things written on their cars, and as for this rich man, he was no different.\n\nWhile in traffic, a netizen noticed a Land Cruiser with a hilarious notice on the motorist looking for baby mamas.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nAt the top left of the car was a notice written:\n\nAs if that was not enough, there was also the age preferred written also at the bottom of the rear windscreen, which one would miss if not keen enough.\n\nRead also\n\nGarissa leader warns boda boda riders against carrying women, lists consequences\n\nIt was not clear on which road the car was cruising, but what was evident was that it was in Nairobi, just minutes away from the city.\n\nThe clip went viral, with some of the ladies noting that they fit the description while the men were in awe of the man\'s genius.\n\nInfluencer Brian Mutinda shared the clip on his Instagram, asking what the exact meaning of \'genty used\' in the sticker was.\n\nHere are some of the reactions shared by netizens:\n\nofficial_njorawww said:\n\nnoni_karanja asked:\n\nsilvah_mistarish said:\n\nmaseka_kembiess asked:\n\nmodern_construction_limited wrote:\n\nsam.kyt said:\n\nRead also\n\nDJ Mo offers KSh 10k reward for help to find TikToker who accused him of being deadbeat\n\nits.tanuii hilariously said:\n\nitsrotich said:\n\nstevenmwalily said:\n\nreels_by_greenlight said:\n\nerick_p.kanyi said:\n\nkarl_254kenya said:\n\nIn another case of a man looking for love, TUKO.co.ke earlier reported the story of a Makueni man, 23, who launched a search for a wife.\n\nSpeaking to TUKO.co.ke, the man, Lawrence, shared certain qualities he wants in his future partner.\n\nThe hustler said he wants a woman between 38 to 45 years old, noting he\'s jobless but wants someone ready to experience love.\n\nHe said he is ready if the woman is a single mum, adding that what he wants is for her to be understanding.\n\nDespite not being able to guarantee anything in the relationship. Lawrence said the lady must be middle-class and working.\n\nProofreading by Mercy Nyambura, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nVictor Otengo (Entertainment editor) Victor Otengo is the Special Projects Lead and Editor at TUKO.co.ke. He attended the Multimedia University of Kenya, where he studied for a Bachelor\'s Degree in Journalism and Mass Communication. He has seven years of experience in journalism and has previously worked as a writer at Standard Digital, reporter and sports pundit at Kwese TV (under African Insights). Email: victor.otengo@tuko.co.ke.\n\nMercy Nyambura (Copyeditor)','News','2025-04-05 08:26:24','2025-04-05 08:26:24',NULL),(31,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/kenya/counties/584702-kakamega-married-man-nursing-injuries-bitten-by-side-chick/','Kakamega: Married Man Nursing Injuries after Being Bitten by Side Chick','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','PAY ATTENTION: Flexible Payment Plans Available! Invest in Yourself & See the Return with Our Affordable Copywriting Course!\n\nFaith Chandianya, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over three years of experience covering politics and Current Affairs in Kenya\n\nKakamega: Douglas Shisia, a 45-year-old man, is recovering at Manyala Subcounty Hospital after being struck and bitten by his side-chick.\n\nThe man, who resides in Nairobi with his wife, travelled to Shiatsala on Wednesday, April 2, to spend time with his 38-year-old side-chick, who is a widow.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nHowever, things took an unexpected turn when Shisia was beaten by his lover and left with injuries\n\nRead also\n\nNairobi lady who went blind after 14-year struggle with diabetes seeks KSh 632k to pay bill\n\nShisia said he tried to defend himself, but the woman was too strong, overpowering him. He is now left with only one upper lip. His loud cries prompted neighbors to come to his rescue.\n\nThe incident was reported to Manyala Police Station, and Shisia is now waiting for the woman’s arrest to seek justice.\n\nRead also\n\nKisumu family appeals for help to find son who left home in 2022\n\nThe doctor in charge at Manyala Sub-County Hospital confirmed the incident, stating that they had treated the patient for lip bites before discharging him.\n\nIn a related incident, a 37-year-old man was killed in Nyatike sub-county, Migori, in what authorities suspect was a love triangle involving a married woman.\n\nThe fatal incident occurred when the deceased arrived at the woman\'s house and found another man there, prompting an altercation.\n\nReports indicated that the married woman was allegedly involved in relationships with both men.\n\nArea chief Voshastar Akal confirmed the incident, stating that the deceased, identified as Kevin Ouma, died from panga injuries, while the other man, Johnson Ochieng, was hospitalised with serious panga wounds.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nSarah Zadock (freelance editor) Sarah Zadock is a Kenyan journalist with over six years of experience. She covers current affairs, specifically politics, alongside human interest news features. Sarah has generated news content for Fourth Estate Online in the Nyanza region, a Migori-based radio station and joined TUKO.co.ke’s correspondents’ network from early 2022. Email: sarazadock111@gmail.com\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 08:26:33','2025-04-05 08:26:33',NULL),(32,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/business-economy/584687-trump-goads-china-beijing-retaliates-global-trade-war/','Trump goads China after Beijing retaliates in global trade war','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nPresident Donald Trump goaded a \"panicked\" China on Friday after the chief US economic rival retaliated against his tariffs and he dismissed stock market panic over the growing global trade war, touting the chance to \"get rich.\"\n\n\"China played it wrong, they panicked -- the one thing they cannot afford to do!\" Trump posted on Truth Social, writing the message in his trademark all-caps.\n\nFor a second day, markets plunged, wiping vast sums off investment and retirement portfolios alike.\n\nWall Street opened with steep selloffs, both the Dow Jones and S&P 500 losing close to three percent. Frankfurt and London sank more than four percent, while Tokyo\'s Nikkei closed 2.8 percent down.\n\nTrump, who unveiled his barrage of import duties against countries all over the world on Wednesday, was unrepentant, posting that \"my policies will never change.\"\n\n\"This is a great time to get rich, richer than ever before,\" he wrote.\n\nRead also\n\nAsian stocks extend global rout after Trump\'s shock tariff blitz\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThe 78-year-old Republican, who was spending a long weekend golfing at his course in Palm Beach, Florida, is banking on the theory that the sheer might of the world\'s biggest economy will force foreign companies to manufacture on US soil, rather than continue to import goods.\n\nHowever, China responded toughly, announcing its own new 34 percent tariffs on US imports starting April 10.\n\nBeijing said it would sue the United States at the World Trade Organization and also restrict export of rare earth elements used in high-end medical and electronics technology.\n\nOther big US trading partners have so far held back as they digest the unfolding international standoff and fears of recession.\n\nEU trade chief Maros Sefcovic was due to speak with US counterparts on Friday.\n\nSefcovic said the EU, which Trump hit with a 20 percent tariff, will act in \"a calm, carefully phased, unified way\" and allow time for talks. However, he also warned the bloc \"won\'t stand idly by, should we be unable to reach a fair deal\".\n\nRead also\n\nWall St leads rout as world reels from Trump tariffs\n\nFrance and Germany have said the 27-nation EU could respond by imposing a tax on US tech companies.\n\nEconomy Minister Eric Lombard urged French companies to show \"patriotism\" after President Emmanuel Macron argued it would send the wrong message if they pressed ahead with investments in the United States.\n\nLombard said the EU\'s retaliation would not necessarily involve tit-for-tat tariffs and could use other tools, pointing to data exchange and tax as levers that could be used.\n\n\"The response can be very strongб but we should not respond with exactly the same weapons the US used as, if we do, it can also have a negative effect in Europe,\" he told news network BFMTV.\n\nIn Tokyo, Prime Minister Shigeru Ishiba called for a \"calm-headed\" approach after Trump slapped 24 percent tariffs on Japanese-made goods.\n\nSeparate US tariffs of 25 percent on all foreign-made cars also went into effect this week, and Canada swiftly responded with a similar levy on US imports.\n\nRead also\n\nGermany slams Trump tariffs, US tech titans in crosshairs\n\nStellantis -- the owner of Jeep, Chrysler and Fiat -- paused production at some Canadian and Mexican assembly plants.\n\nJapanese carmaker Nissan said on Friday it would revise plans to reduce production in the United States.\n\nThe company also said it would stop selling two vehicle models on the US market that are made at a factory in Mexico.\n\nSweden\'s Volvo Cars, owned by China\'s Geely, said it would increase its production of vehicles in the United States and probably produce an additional model there.\n\nAmid howls of protest abroad, and even from some of Trump\'s Republicans who fear price rises at home, Commerce Secretary Howard Lutnick urged patience.\n\n\"Let Donald Trump run the global economy. He knows what he\'s doing,\" Lutnick said on CNN.\n\nSource: AFP\n\nAFP AFP text, photo, graphic, audio or video material shall not be published, broadcast, rewritten for broadcast or publication or redistributed directly or indirectly in any medium. AFP news material may not be stored in whole or in part in a computer or otherwise except for personal and non-commercial use. AFP will not be held liable for any delays, inaccuracies, errors or omissions in any AFP news material or in transmission or delivery of all or any part thereof or for any damages whatsoever. As a newswire service, AFP does not obtain releases from subjects, individuals, groups or entities contained in its photographs, videos, graphics or quoted in its texts. Further, no clearance is obtained from the owners of any trademarks or copyrighted materials whose marks and materials are included in AFP material. Therefore you will be solely responsible for obtaining any and all necessary releases from whatever individuals and/or entities necessary for any uses of AFP material.','News','2025-04-05 08:26:55','2025-04-05 08:26:55',NULL),(33,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/politics/584647-justin-muturi-ruto-unfit-president-claims-s-corrupt-dangerous-character/','Justin Muturi Says Ruto Is Unfit to Be President, Claims He\'s Corrupt: \"Dangerous Character\"','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: Why Wait for Opportunities to Come to You? Master Copywriting Today, So You Can Start Earning Tomorrow\n\nDidacus Malowa, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over three years of experience covering politics and current affairs in Kenya.\n\nNairobi - Former Attorney General and Public Service CS Justin Muturi has delivered a verdict on President William Ruto\'s leadership, branding him \"irredeemably corrupt.\"\n\nIn a scathing interview on Friday, April 4, the former Cabinet secretary and ex-speaker of the National Assembly launched a blistering attack on Ruto, stating that he\'s unfit for the presidency.\n\nRead also\n\nJustin Muturi discloses he initially turned down William Ruto\'s job offer as AG\n\nMuturi claimed that Ruto’s dual personality makes him a “dangerous character,” questioning the integrity of the head of state.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nHe did not hold back in expressing his belief that Ruto was not fit to hold the highest office in the land.\n\nMuturi further criticised Ruto’s stance on corruption, calling out the apparent contradiction between the president\'s public anti-corruption rhetoric and his alleged involvement in corrupt activities.\n\nRead also\n\nWilliam Ruto continues onslaught against Gachagua, says he suffered working with him: \"Nilihangaika\"\n\nIn what many will view as a highly controversial statement, Muturi accused Ruto of being “irredeemably corrupt.”\n\nWhen directly asked whether Ruto was corrupt, Muturi responded without hesitation, saying, “Absolutely. Very. Irredeemably corrupt.”\n\nMuturi went on to reference the controversial Adani deal, a subject that has caused a stir in political circles.\n\nHe claimed that Ruto was directly involved in the deal, alleging that the president’s advisor, Adan Mohamed, had provided him with information linking Ruto to the deal, particularly concerning the airport project.\n\nRead also\n\nKenyans shower Justin Muturi with praises as he hands over office to Mudavadi: “Unbowed”\n\nIn response to Ruto\'s recent allegations that he neglected his duties, Muturi strongly rejected the claims.\n\nHe clarified that his dismissal was not due to negligence but rather his outspoken stance against extrajudicial killings and abductions.\n\nMuturi revealed that he had sent private letters to Ruto, urging the government to address the rising issue of kidnappings in Cabinet meetings.\n\nHe emphasized that his commitment to justice and human rights had led to his removal, highlighting his efforts to bring attention to these grave concerns within the government.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nDidacus Malowa (Political and current affairs editor) Didacus Malowa is a political and current affairs editor at TUKO.co.ke. He holds a Bachelor\'s Degree in Communication and Media Technology with IT from Maseno University in 2021. He has over two years of experience in digital journalism. Email: didacus.malowa@tuko.co.ke\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 08:27:03','2025-04-05 08:27:03',NULL),(34,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/editorial/opinion/584675-i-send-money-home-im-met-negativity-curses-nifanyeje-expert-advises/','\"I Send Money Home Yet I’m Met with Negativity and Curses, What Can I Do?\": Expert Advises','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: How to Secure Copywriting Gigs Fast – So You Can Turn Words Into Money Right Now\n\nAnonymous wrote:\n\nRead also\n\n\"I feel trapped under my aunt\'s control, what should I do?\": Expert advises\n\nAllan Lawrence is a renowned counselling psychologist, relationship coach, and author, known for his expertise in relationship dynamics and personal growth. He is a sought-after conference speaker, both locally and internationally.\n\nLawrence advised the lady to take a step back and reflect before making any impulsive decisions.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nHe acknowledged the emotional weight of the situation and offered guidance on how to manage the conflicting pressures.\n\nHe also advised focusing on self-care and seeking support, whether from a therapist or a trusted friend, to regain clarity.\n\nRead also\n\nLady painfully narrates being dumped by boyfriend of 6 years, leaks WhatsApp chats\n\nIn terms of the strained relationship with her parent, Lawrence suggested that the lady consider setting clear boundaries and protecting her mental health.\n\nLastly, Lawrence encouraged the lady to recognise the strength in her ability to help others, despite her own struggles.\n\nRead also\n\nKenyan student’s heartbreaking betrayal turns into unbelievable blessing, Expert advises\n\nDisclaimer: Advice provided in this article is general and should not replace professional guidance based on individual circumstances. For personalized advice, it is recommended to consult a qualified professional.\n\nGot a story to share or need professional advice? Reach out to us at askanexpert@tuko.co.ke with \"Ask The Expert\" in the subject line.\n\nEarlier, TUKO.co.ke reported that a 21-year-old woman had opened up about feeling trapped under her aunt’s strict control, despite being an adult.\n\nTaken in as a child due to medical issues, she said the once-caring guardian has become emotionally and physically abusive, manipulating her and denying her independence.\n\nEven after acquiring her ID at 19, the young woman said she was still being treated like an unpaid servant, with her aunt refusing to let go of control.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nLinda Amiani (editorial assistant) Linda Amiani is a dedicated Multimedia Journalist and Editorial Assistant at Tuko.co.ke. With a solid background in broadcast journalism and over four years of experience, she has made significant contributions to the media industry through her writing, editing, and content creation. Email: linda.amiani@tuko.co.ke\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 08:27:12','2025-04-05 08:27:12',NULL),(35,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/politics/584146-william-ruto-names-leaders-gachagua-clashed-impeachment-kila-siku-ilikuwa-kesi/','William Ruto Names Leaders Gachagua Clashed with Before Impeachment: \"Kila Siku Ilikuwa Kesi\"','2001-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nTUKO.co.ke journalist Ivan Mboto has over three years of experience reporting on politics and current affairs in Kenya\n\nPresident William Ruto has opened up about his troubled working relationship with his former deputy, Rigathi Gachagua.\n\nRuto detailed how the latter frequently clashed with junior government officials. Speaking during an interview with media houses ahead of his Mt. Kenya tour, Ruto painted a picture of a strained partnership characterised by incessant conflicts and internal wrangles.\n\nRead also\n\nWilliam Ruto scoffs at journalist for questioning him over absence of Gachagua\'s allies\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nHowever, the conflicts did not end there.\n\nAccording to Ruto, Gachagua soon turned his attention to youthful leaders within the United Democratic Alliance (UDA), including Kiharu MP Ndindi Nyoro.\n\nThe President said he eventually confronted Gachagua and urged him to focus on national development instead of personal battles.\n\nRead also\n\nWilliam Ruto showers Ndindi Nyoro with praises, explains why he was replaced: \"Fine gentleman\"\n\nRuto further accused Gachagua of attempting to exert undue influence over UDA MPs by demanding loyalty and asserting his authority.\n\nBeyond the internal wrangles, Ruto criticised Gachagua for failing to communicate the government’s progress and achievements to the public.\n\nThe President contrasted Gachagua’s approach with his own tenure as deputy president under Uhuru Kenyatta.\n\nRead also\n\nWilliam Ruto claims Rigathi Gachagua demanded KSh 10b: “I said I’ll not do it”\n\nIn a related development, the head of state revealed another reason behind his fallout with Gachagua, accusing him of blackmail and threats to undermine his presidency.\n\nRuto claimed Gachagua demanded KSh 10 billion to secure support for him in the Mt Kenya region.\n\nAccording to Ruto, Gachagua warned that without the funds, he would work to limit his presidency to a single term. The president stated that the former DP directly told him on his face that he could influence his political fate.\n\nProofreading by Jackson Otukho, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nHarry Ivan Mboto (Current affairs editor) Harry Ivan Mboto is an accredited journalist with the Media Council of Kenya (MCK) and a Current Affairs and Politics Editor at TUKO. He is a Linguistics, Media, and Communication student at Moi University and has over three years of experience in digital journalism. Have a news tip, query, or feedback? Reach him at: harry.ivan@tuko.co.ke.\n\nJackson Otukho (Copyeditor) Jackson Otukho is a multi-media journalist and current affairs editor at TUKO.co.ke. In 2019, he graduated with a Bachelor of Science degree in Media Science from Moi University. He has over seven years of experience in digital and print media. He initially worked as a news editor at Standard Media Group (2014-2017) and Citizen TV (2019 May- 2019 September). Through his career, he has won several awards, including the editor with the cleanest copy and with the most social media engagement. Mail: jackson.otukho@tuko.co.ke','News','2025-04-05 08:27:22','2025-04-05 08:27:22',NULL),(36,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/business-economy/584680-us-hiring-beats-expectations-march-tariff-uncertainty-brews/','US hiring beats expectations in March as tariff uncertainty brews','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Don\'t miss out! Join Tuko.co.ke Sports News channel on WhatsApp now!\n\nHiring in the United States was stronger than expected in March, government data showed Friday, even as uncertainty brewed over the wider effects of President Donald Trump\'s tariffs and other policies.\n\nThe world\'s biggest economy added 228,000 jobs last month, much more than analysts anticipated and significantly above February\'s revised 117,000 figure, said the Department of Labor.\n\nThe jobless rate meanwhile edged up to 4.2 percent, from 4.1 percent in February.\n\nTrump said in a social media post that these were \"great job numbers, far better than expected.\"\n\n\"It\'s already working,\" he added, referring to his policies.\n\n\"The President\'s push to onshore jobs here in the United States is working,\" White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt said in a separate statement, pointing to job growth in areas like transportation.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nSince January, the Trump administration has embarked on wide-ranging job cuts to the federal government, while the president also unleashed steep tariffs targeting allies and adversaries alike.\n\nRead also\n\nTrump tariffs to test resiliency of US consumers\n\nBut economists expect it will take time for the full effects of his policies to ripple through the economy, warning of higher consumer prices and an impact on growth.\n\nThe hiring number showed that the jobs market remained robust for now, and it was notably above the 130,000 figure that analysts expected, according to Briefing.com.\n\nSectors that saw job gains included health care and social assistance, as well as retail trade -- \"partially reflecting the return of workers from a strike,\" the report said.\n\nBut federal government employment declined by 4,000 in March, following the loss of 11,000 jobs in February.\n\nAverage hourly earnings grew 0.3 percent in March to $36.00, picking up slightly from February\'s pace.\n\n\"In light of the tariff announcements this week and the sharp drop in stock markets around the world in response, these data are likely not capturing the moment with respect to the actual strength of the economy,\" warned chief economist Mike Fratantoni of the Mortgage Bankers Association.\n\nRead also\n\nUK avoids worst US tariffs post-Brexit, but no celebrations\n\nLooking ahead, economists are monitoring the effects of sweeping tariffs that Trump imposed on some of the biggest US trading partners in March, alongside even broader action set to take effect in April.\n\nOn Wednesday, Trump announced a 10 percent tariff on most US trading partners, set to take effect Saturday.\n\n\"The impact of these tariffs is unknown but most economists would say this is a huge disruption,\" said Dan North, senior economist at Allianz Trade North America.\n\n\"It\'s the uncertainty itself that is now a driving force economically,\" he told AFP.\n\nApart from adding to consumer costs in the near-term, North expects the tariffs could also \"put a damper on job growth\" and weigh on the labor market as well.\n\nSource: AFP\n\nAFP AFP text, photo, graphic, audio or video material shall not be published, broadcast, rewritten for broadcast or publication or redistributed directly or indirectly in any medium. AFP news material may not be stored in whole or in part in a computer or otherwise except for personal and non-commercial use. AFP will not be held liable for any delays, inaccuracies, errors or omissions in any AFP news material or in transmission or delivery of all or any part thereof or for any damages whatsoever. As a newswire service, AFP does not obtain releases from subjects, individuals, groups or entities contained in its photographs, videos, graphics or quoted in its texts. Further, no clearance is obtained from the owners of any trademarks or copyrighted materials whose marks and materials are included in AFP material. Therefore you will be solely responsible for obtaining any and all necessary releases from whatever individuals and/or entities necessary for any uses of AFP material.','News','2025-04-05 08:27:57','2025-04-05 08:27:57',NULL),(37,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/business-economy/584646-justin-muturi-discloses-initially-turned-william-rutos-job-offer-ag/','Justin Muturi Discloses He Initially Turned Down William Ruto\'s Job Offer as AG','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: How to Secure Copywriting Gigs Fast – So You Can Turn Words Into Money Right Now\n\nJaphet Ruto, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over eight years of experience in finance, business, and technology, delivering insightful analysis of economic trends in Kenya and globally.\n\nFormer Public Service Cabinet secretary (CS) Justin Muturi has revealed he initially turned down President William Ruto\'s job offer to serve as Kenya\'s attorney general.\n\nMuturi disclosed he was uncomfortable with the position that came with huge responsibilities as he had served as National Assembly speaker for two terms.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nSpeaking to NTV on Friday, April 4, the politician noted he wanted to be a CS with fewer duties.\n\nRead also\n\nJustin Muturi says Ruto is unfit to be president, claims he\'s corrupt: \"Dangerous character\"\n\nDays later, Muturi revealed Ruto appealed to him through his successor Moses Wetang\'ula to accept the job.\n\nWhen he declined it, the president summoned him to State House, Nairobi and convinced him.\n\nRead also\n\nWilliam Ruto hints at backing Kindiki in 2032: \"Si mimi nilikuwa yes man wa Uhuru?\"\n\nAfter being sacked, Muturi described Ruto as \'corrupt\' and claimed he\'s unfit to hold the office.\n\nRuto publicly criticised Muturi, describing his time as AG \"fairly incompetent\" in addressing important legal issues, such as the Waqf Commission\'s formation.\n\nMuturi, who was AG from 2022 to 2024, was fired along with the majority of Ruto\'s Cabinet after the historic June 25, 2024, protests spearheaded by Generation Z.\n\nAfter being named as Public Service CS, he often disagreed with the president on several issues, including extrajudicial killings and kidnappings.\n\nRead also\n\nJustin Muturi Claims He Was Ambushed by Letter to Hand Over Office to Musalia Mudavadi\n\nAs a result, the president fired him and accused him of absconding duty by missing Cabinet sessions.\n\nMuturi will get lucrative perks following his exit from the public service.\n\nA retired speaker is eligible for a pension and other lifetime benefits under the Retirement Benefits Act of 2015.\n\nMuturi\'s pension for the job is equivalent to 80% of his last month\'s salary when he was employed.\n\nAdditionally, he will get a lump sum payment equivalent to one year\'s wages for each term he served - in his case, two terms.\n\nHe will receive KSh 3.5 million in gratuity for serving as CS, speaker and attorney general.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nJaphet Ruto (Current Affairs and Business Editor) Japhet Ruto is an award-winning TUKO.co.ke journalist with over eight years of working experience in the media industry. Ruto graduated from Moi University in 2015 with a Bachelor’s Degree in Communication and Journalism. He is a Business & Tech Editor. Ruto won the 2019 BAKE Awards’ Agriculture Blog of the Year. He was named TUKO.co.ke\'s best current affairs editor in 2020 and 2021. In 2022 and 2023, he was TUKO.co.ke\'s best business editor. He completed the Experimenting with new formats and Advance digital reporting curriculum from Google News Initiative. Email: japhet.ruto@tuko.co.ke.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 08:28:17','2025-04-05 08:28:17',NULL),(38,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/kenya/counties/584732-trans-nzoia-21-year-woman-dies-delivery-alleged-medical-negligence/','Trans Nzoia: 21-Year-Old Woman Dies During Delivery Amid Alleged Medical Negligence','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: How to Start Earning with Copywriting in Just 7 Days – Even if You’re a Complete Beginner\n\nTUKO.co.ke journalist Ivan Mboto has over three years of experience reporting on politics and current affairs in Kenya\n\nA family in Tuwan estate on the outskirts of Kitale town in Trans Nzoia County is mourning the passing on of their 21-year old daughter, Ashley Aluoch.\n\nAluoch, who was due for delivery in two weeks died at Wamalwa Kijana Teaching and Referral Hospital due to alleged medical negligence after admission.\n\nWhen she was examined, it was established that Ashley had lost her foetus and she need urgent induced labour.\n\nRead also\n\nMum whose newborn was reportedly switched in hospital speaks after DNA results: \"Sio wangu\"\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nAfter still birth, Ashley needed three pints of blood which was not available at the facility.\n\nKitale blood satellite domiciled at Doctors\' Plaza is less than three kilometres from the incomplete referral hospital.\n\nDouglas Mafabi, father to Ashley said her daughter was admitted to the hospital and left unattended for about 34 hours.\n\nFollowing her death, angry residents of Tuwan and Mitume estates stormed into the level IV hospital demanding answers from the management.\n\nResponding to the allegations Isaac Kisiangani the director of Health in Trans Nzoia County said the lady lost her foetus in the uterus three before she arrived at the hospital.\n\nRead also\n\nKisumu: Mother arrested for scalding son with boiling water for allegedly stealing 2kg of maize\n\nOn her part, Judith Nasimiyu, the chief officer in charge of health dismissed the allegations that there was negligence.\n\nNasimiyu said that the patient was attended to by a team of three medics from the time she was admitted to the day she passed on.\n\nIn a related story TUKO.co.ke previously covered, a 27-year-old expectant mother, Phanice Ratemo, tragically died at Magena Dispensary in Kisii County after reportedly being neglected by medical staff during labour.\n\nRatemo had been admitted to the facility late at night, complaining of labour pains. However, her repeated calls for assistance allegedly went unanswered, with nurses insisting her time to deliver had not yet come.\n\nRead also\n\nNakuru mother of 3 cries for help to pay husband\'s KSh 560k bill, secure release of his body\n\nAccording to sources, Ratemo began bleeding after her water broke, but no medics came to her aid. She eventually died alongside her unborn child. The situation worsened when staff at the facility allegedly fled upon learning of her death, leaving her body behind.\n\nStory by Emanuel Tarus, a TUKO.co.ke correspondent\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nHarry Ivan Mboto (Current affairs editor) Harry Ivan Mboto is an accredited journalist with the Media Council of Kenya (MCK) and a Current Affairs and Politics Editor at TUKO. He is a Linguistics, Media, and Communication student at Moi University and has over three years of experience in digital journalism. Have a news tip, query, or feedback? Reach him at: harry.ivan@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 08:28:25','2025-04-05 08:28:25',NULL),(39,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/politics/584669-kalonzo-musyoka-sets-record-straight-attack-raila-working-govt/','Kalonzo Musyoka Sets Record Straight on Why He Can Never Attack Raila Despite Working with Govt','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: How to Start Earning with Copywriting in Just 7 Days – Even if You’re a Complete Beginner\n\nFaith Chandianya, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over three years of experience covering politics and Current Affairs in Kenya\n\nWiper party leader Kalonzo Musyoka has explained why he would never attack or disrespect Orange Democratic Movement (ODM) leader Raila Odinga.\n\nThis is despite Raila\'s decision to work with the Kenya Kwanza government, which he had strongly opposed.\n\nWhile speaking at the Umoja Summit Party\'s Annual Delegates Convention on Thursday, April 3, he stated that he could never bring himself to attack those he has worked with.\n\nRead also\n\nKenyan newspapers review: Raila Odinga cries as he mourns loyal aide George Odour\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nHe affirmed that it is simply his nature to maintain mutual respect with former colleagues, even if they go in a different direction.\n\nWhile seemingly addressing whether Azimio still exists, Kalonzo said that when Raila-led ODM signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with President William Ruto’s United Democratic Alliance (UDA), he knew the Azimio Coalition had ended.\n\nHe further stated that his conclusion was realistic, as he believed the Wiper Democratic Movement cannot be the only party in Azimio.\n\nThis follows a letter from Kalonzo to Raila, raising concerns over the fairness of the process to select new commissioners for the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC).\n\nRead also\n\nMurang\'a: Blow to Gachagua as Maragua MP ditches his camp, declares support for Ruto\n\nHe argued that the IEBC issue was one of the topics discussed during the National Dialogue Committee (NADCO) engagements.\n\nKalonzo further expressed concern over the apparent omission of the electoral body\'s reconstitution in the 10-point agenda that Ruto and Raila agreed upon when they decided to work together for the country\'s betterment.\n\nHowever, the former vice president reiterated his commitment to waiting and observing how the IEBC selection process unfolds before deciding on his next step.\n\nDays later, ODM party secretary general Edwin Sifuna accused Kalonzo of attempting to delay the IEBC reconstitution process.\n\nSifuna also denied Kalonzo\'s claims that ODM is working with UDA in orderto manipulate the process.\n\nHe disclosed that one of the individuals shortlisted for the IEBC position is his advisor, maintaining that the candidate had every right to seek the role.\n\nThe secretary general emphasised that the IEBC selection panel is functioning independently in accordance with the law, cautioning against early political interference intended to undermine the process.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nFaith Chandianya (CA editor) Faith Chandianya is a multi-media journalist and a Current Affairs Editor at TUKO.co.ke. In 2023, she graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Media Science from Moi University. She has over four years experience in digital journalism. Email: Faith.Chandianya@tuko.co.ke\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 08:28:34','2025-04-05 08:28:34',NULL),(40,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/business-economy/584713-kenya-renews-gulf-oil-import-deal-secures-pump-prices/','Kenya Renews Gulf Oil Import Deal, Secures Lower Pump Prices','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nJaphet Ruto is a journalist at TUKO.co.ke with over eight years of experience reporting on finance, business, and technology. He provides insightful analysis of economic trends in Kenya and globally.\n\nThree state-owned Gulf companies have agreed to cut petroleum prices under an extended fuel supply deal with Kenya, offering relief to consumers at the pump.\n\nKenya will now purchase a tonne of diesel from Saudi Aramco, Abu Dhabi National Oil Company, and Emirates National Oil Company for $78 (KSh 10,081.50 at the current exchange rate) under the new government-to-government (G-to-G) agreement.\n\nRead also\n\nKenya overtakes Nigeria, Ghana, Uganda, TZ as the largest mitumba destination in Africa\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThis represents an 11.3% decrease from the current price of $88 (KSh 11,374), while the price of petrol will drop from $90 (KSh 11,632.50) to $84 (KSh 10,857).\n\nBloomberg reported that freight and premium prices for jet fuel will decline by 13% to $97 (KSh 12537.25).\n\nDaniel Kiptoo, the director general of the Energy and Petroleum Regulatory Authority (EPRA), announced that Saudi Aramco, Emirates National Oil, and Abu Dhabi National Oil will continue to supply Nairobi with petrol, diesel, kerosene, and jet fuel under a 180-day credit plan.\n\nAccording to Kiptoo, the contract renewal will start at the end of 2025, following Kenya\'s completion of importing the already negotiated shipments.\n\nPreviously, Kenya had extended the agreement for oil supplies to the end of 2024.\n\nIn the last 10 years, trade between Kenya and the United Arab Emirates (UAE) has more than doubled.\n\nRead also\n\nTreasury CS John Mbadi leads Kenyan delegation in China to scout for deals\n\nUAE is Kenya\'s second-largest import market and the sixth-largest export market.\n\nKiptoo explained that Uganda\'s move to source its petroleum directly after terminating its prior agreement with Kenya was the reason for the delay in shipping the remaining oil consignment into the nation.\n\nThe EPRA boss expressed approval of the G-to-G deal, pointing out that the imports on credit helped stabilise the shilling\'s value relative to other major world currencies, such as the US dollar.\n\nAccording to the Central Bank of Kenya (CBK) the value of the local currency has increased by 17%, since the implementation of the deal.\n\nOn Thursday, April 3, CBK quoted the shilling at 129.25 per unit against the US dollar.\n\nEPRA irked Kenyans by maintaining fuel prices on Friday, March 14. The announcement came after the price of crude oil fell by 16% globally.\n\nRead also\n\nFormer Jubilee Party headquarters building in Nairobi to be auctioned on May 6\n\nThe regulator kept the retail prices of petrol, diesel, and kerosene in Nairobi at KSh 176.58, KSh 167.06, and KSh 151.39, respectively.\n\nDuring the period under review, the average landing cost of imported super petrol increased by 1.34%.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nJaphet Ruto (Current Affairs and Business Editor) Japhet Ruto is an award-winning TUKO.co.ke journalist with over eight years of working experience in the media industry. Ruto graduated from Moi University in 2015 with a Bachelor’s Degree in Communication and Journalism. He is a Business & Tech Editor. Ruto won the 2019 BAKE Awards’ Agriculture Blog of the Year. He was named TUKO.co.ke\'s best current affairs editor in 2020 and 2021. In 2022 and 2023, he was TUKO.co.ke\'s best business editor. He completed the Experimenting with new formats and Advance digital reporting curriculum from Google News Initiative. Email: japhet.ruto@tuko.co.ke.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 08:28:43','2025-04-05 08:28:43',NULL),(41,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/407344-condolence-messages-loss-a-great-leader-boss.html','100+ condolence messages for loss of a great leader or boss','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Death and grief are part of human experiences. When a renowned person dies, the masses feel sad and mourn with the family. Condolence messages for loss of a great leader or boss start pouring in immediately after the famous person\'s death is announced. People share messages of sympathy with the family and friends of the deceased.\n\nIt may be challenging to find the appropriate condolences for an email, note, or text message. Sending sympathies can let the individual know that you care about their grief. Here is a look at some great condolence messages for the loss of a great leader or boss.\n\nRead also\n\n70 thoughtful condolence messages for a coworker who lost someone\n\nA boss is a leader whether they were governing a small group of people or a huge corporation. When a boss dies, the gap is felt by the people that looked up to him. When composing a message to express condolences to your boss’s family, try and mention how well he worked with his juniors.\n\nHere are some great examples;\n\nRead also\n\nWhat to say to a woman who has lost her husband: 100+ condolence messages\n\nThe loss of a boss is heartbreaking. Their guidance and wisdom leave a lasting impact. In times of grief, sharing kind words brings comfort. Condolence messages for loss of a great leader or boss express respect, gratitude, and sorrow. This tribute honors their legacy and the inspiration they gave us.\n\nHere are death condolence messages for a great boss;\n\nRead also\n\n20 short prayers to comfort a grieving friend who is coping with grief\n\nMany people struggle with how to say sorry for their loss professionally. When writing a condolence message to mourn your boss, consider the words you use and how the family may perceive them. Don\'t be too casual with the message unless you were close friends with the boss.\n\nUse the examples below to write a condolence message to the family of a deceased leader\n\nRead also\n\n50+ painful messages to a cheating husband to tell him he hurt you\n\nExpressing condolences professionally requires a balance of empathy, respect, and sincerity. When offering condolence messages for loss of a great leader or boss, it\'s essential to acknowledge their impact. Extend support to colleagues or family, and keep the message heartfelt yet professional.\n\nSo what do you write when a leader dies? Here’s how to convey your sympathy appropriately in different settings.\n\nRead also\n\nCondolence messages for loss of father of a friend or coworker\n\nThe passing of a colleague leaves a void in both the workplace and our hearts. In these moments of sorrow, extending a thoughtful condolence message can offer solace and strength. It’s an opportunity to honor their legacy, support those affected, and express empathy.\n\nRead also\n\n100+ RIP brother quotes, messages, and condolences to share\n\nA condolence message could either be long or short. Long rest in peace messages need one to reflect on the kind of leader the boss was. You can share religious sympathy messages that are only two words long.\n\nSend your heartfelt condolences to your late boss with the messages below;\n\nRead also\n\nTribute to a late uncle: Sad and touching farewell messages\n\nLosing a father is a deep and personal loss. It’s difficult to find the right words. Expressing sympathy shows respect and support. A thoughtful message can bring comfort. These condolence messages help you offer kindness and strength.\n\nShare them with your boss to show you care during this tough time.\n\nRead also\n\nGoodbye cousin quotes, tributes, messages, and R.I.P quotes\n\nLosing a mother is an immense sorrow, and when it happens to your boss, offering heartfelt condolences shows support and respect. A thoughtful message can provide comfort during this difficult time.\n\nHere are some sincere condolence messages to help you express sympathy and let your boss know they are not alone.\n\nRead also\n\n50+ condolence messages to a friend who lost her husband\n\nMessages of condolence can be unique to show sincerity. Here are some examples:\n\nRead also\n\n50+ heartfelt condolence messages for the loss of a sister\n\nMessages have been shown to bring great comfort to people grieving. You can express your care through a thoughtful text message. Find a fitting condolence message above and share it with the person to remind them they are not alone.\n\nPeople grieve in different ways, and one way is sharing messages of condolences and celebration of the life of the departed. Both known people and those unknown by many have families that feel the loss when they die. People pay more attention when writing condolence messages for loss of a great leader or boss because the messages get viewed by the masses.\n\nTuko.co.ke recently shared 100+ awesome profile pic comments for Facebook. Dropping a comment on someone\'s picture is a kind gesture, and everyone appreciates it. However, some comments will bring joy, whereas others will not.\n\nIt takes creativity and an open mind to write a remarkable comment on someone\'s picture. Some people find it hard to do it, and that is why some of these fantastic profile pic comments for Facebook will help.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nVenic Nyanchama (Lifestyle writer) Venic Nyanchama is an editor with more than three years of working experience in journalism. She has an educational background in Journalism and Media Studies from the University of Nairobi, having graduated in 2014. Venic has worked on different platforms, such as Rumour Juice and Yen.com.gh. Her content encompasses celebrity biographies, education, guides, fashion, and gaming. In 2023, Venic finished the AFP course on Digital Investigation Techniques and the Google News Initiative. You can reach her via venicmwendwa@gmail.com.\n\nSharon Boit (Lifestyle writer) Sharon J. Boit is a Lifestyle Writer at Legit Media Holdings, working on content optimisation since October 2024. Sharon began her career as a researcher and project manager at the Center for Urban Research and Innovations, University of Nairobi, for 4 years. In 2019, she became a freelance SEO content writer, writing blog posts and articles on travel, pets, online sports betting, personal finance, lifestyle, radio news, and technology. You can reach Sharon J. Boit by email at boit@gmail.com.','News','2025-04-05 08:28:52','2025-04-05 08:28:52',NULL),(42,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/politics/584731-john-mbadi-slams-nyanza-leaders-unnecessary-noise-urges-focus-governance/','John Mbadi Slams Nyanza Leaders Over Unnecessary Noise, Urges Focus on Governance','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: You’re One Course Away from Transforming Your Life. Learn Copywriting and Turn Your Passion into Profit\n\nFaith Chandianya, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over three years of experience covering politics and Current Affairs in Kenya\n\nMigori: National Treasury Cabinet secretary John Mbadi on Friday, April 4, criticised Nyanza leaders for what he described as persistent disruptions and unnecessary noise.\n\nSpeaking at Migori Teachers Training College during its 35th graduation ceremony on Friday, April 4, Mbadi said the leaders appeared disoriented in their actions.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nRead also\n\nKenya newspapers review: William Ruto says he’s unstoppable in 2027 as he rallies support in Mt Kenya\n\nHe urged them to remain silent, and if they must speak, to do so in a manner befitting leaders in a great government.\n\nHe also noted that leaders from the region are making too many demands that cannot be fulfilled all at once.\n\nHe further noted that in Kenya, only two positions hold significant power, the one with authority and the one who signs the documents.\n\nThe CS urged the leaders to leverage the authority of the president, who has already given his support, to ensure development reaches the region.\n\nRead also\n\nRuto vows to deliver for Mt Kenya, says he remembers their support: \"Mimi si wazimu nisahau\"\n\nHe also urged Migori leaders to stop exerting political pressure and allow the elected officials to do their work.\n\nMbadi’s remarks were echoed by Nyatike MP Tom Odege, who stressed that the growing political tensions in Migori are doing more harm than good to its residents.\n\nPolitical tensions in Migori have been high, leading to chaos, with the latest incident occurring at Migori Stadium between factions supporting Governor Ochillo Ayacko and Uriri MP Mark Nyamita.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nSarah Zadock (freelance editor) Sarah Zadock is a Kenyan journalist with over six years of experience. She covers current affairs, specifically politics, alongside human interest news features. Sarah has generated news content for Fourth Estate Online in the Nyanza region, a Migori-based radio station and joined TUKO.co.ke’s correspondents’ network from early 2022. Email: sarazadock111@gmail.com\n\nFaith Chandianya (CA editor) Faith Chandianya is a multi-media journalist and a Current Affairs Editor at TUKO.co.ke. In 2023, she graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Media Science from Moi University. She has over four years experience in digital journalism. Email: Faith.Chandianya@tuko.co.ke','News','2025-04-05 08:29:01','2025-04-05 08:29:01',NULL),(43,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/sports/571473-who-lexi-thompsons-husband-what-dating-life/','Who is Lexi Thompson\'s husband? What we know about her dating life','2006-01-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Lexi Thompson is a celebrated American professional golfer. She is renowned for her impressive career on the LPGA Tour, where she has achieved significant success and recognition. Her status as one of the top female golfers has sparked curiosity about her personal life, with fans eager to know more. So, is she married? And if so, who is Lexi Thompson\'s husband?\n\nLexi Thompson is known for being private about her love life. However, she surprised everyone by attending the Solheim Cup gala night in September 2024 with a mystery man. Her appearance at the event generated interest in her dating life, as she declared herself single months earlier. What happened, and what is Lexi Thompson\'s relationship status?\n\nRead also\n\nWho is Sophie Cunningham\'s partner? All about her dating life\n\nAs of this writing, Lexi Thompson is not married. She is believed to be in a relationship with Max Provost, the mystery man with whom she attended the Solheim Cup gala night on September 12 2024. USA Today\'s Golf Week revealed the mystery man\'s name as Max Provost while publishing photos from the event. However, Lexi has not yet confirmed their relationship.\n\nAccording to Essentially Sports, Lexi has always been secretive about her dating life, offering no information to the media or the public. She had previously (in February 2024) revealed being single amid marriage rumours. However, since announcing her retirement on May 28, 2024, and mentioning her desire to settle down, Thompson\'s stance on being single might have changed.\n\nHere is what Lexi told the Ladies European Tour about her retirement plans. She said,\n\nRead also\n\nRyan Blaney\'s wife: Is the NASCAR driver married to Gianna Tulio?\n\nShe added,\n\nLexi Thompson\'s partner, Max Provost, is a Clinical Sales Representative at Intuitive Surgical in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. Per his LinkedIn profile, Provost holds a Bachelor\'s in Marketing from Florida State University\'s College of Business.\n\nBut apart from his education and career, not much else is known about Lexi\'s partner, Max Provost. It is also unknown where the pair met and how long they have been dating.\n\nLexi Thompson and Gerrod Chadwell have never dated. Gerrod, the head coach of the Texas A&M Aggies women\'s golf team since 2021, is married to Stacy Lewis, an American professional golfer and a 13-time winner on the LPGA Tour. Gerrod and Stacy tied the knot on August 6, 2016, and have one child, Chesnee Lynn Chadwell (born in October 2018).\n\nRead also\n\nAll about Pete Davidson\'s mom, Amy Waters Davidson, of Irish descent\n\nLexi Thompson does not have any children. The rumours began in December 2023 after she posted a photo on Instagram holding a baby. However, based on the post, the baby is her nephew, Maverick Cole Thompson, her brother Curtis\'s son, not her child.\n\nRead also\n\nMeet Lamelo Ball\'s girlfriend, Ana Montana, a social media influencer\n\nMany fans are curious about Lexi Thompson\'s husband, but she has kept her love life private. Currently believed to be dating, the professional golfer has not revealed details about her relationships. However, Lexi has expressed her desire to settle down, get married, and start a family someday. Until then, she remains focused on finishing her career and personal growth.\n\nAre you looking for more information about Liv Morgan\'s love life? Tuko.co.ke featured an insightful article exploring the WWE star\'s relationship history and love life.\n\nThe American professional wrestler and actress has gained immense popularity for her exceptional skills, making her one of the most celebrated names in wrestling. But besides her career, what else do you know about Liv Morgan? Is she married?\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nSimon Ayub (Lifestyle writer) Simon Ayub is a Content Manager, Strategist, and writer who joined Tuko\'s team in 2019. He graduated in 2014 with a BSc in Agricultural Economics and is a CPA. Simon has over a decade of experience creating content for nyagah.co.ke, the Hoth and other platforms. He works on content encompassing biographies, fashion and lifestyle, gaming, and more. Simon was awarded the \"Writer of the Year\" 2024 on Tuko. In 2023, Simon finished the AFP course on Digital Investigation Techniques and, in 2024, expanded their skills through the Google Initiative Course. You can reach him via simonayub@gmail.com.','News','2025-04-05 08:29:12','2025-04-05 08:29:12',NULL),(44,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/politics/584717-drama-section-embu-youth-shut-william-ruto-tour-uongo-uongo/','Drama as Hostile Embu Residents Confront William Ruto During Tour: \"Uongo, Uongo\"','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','PAY ATTENTION: Flexible Payment Plans Available! Invest in Yourself & See the Return with Our Affordable Copywriting Course!\n\nDidacus Malowa, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over three years of experience covering politics and current affairs in Kenya.\n\nEmbu - President William Ruto\'s week-long tour of Mt Kenya has been successful for the most part as he tours the vote-rich region.\n\nAhead of the tour, his critics claimed he had completely lost grip of the region, suggesting he might get a cold welcome.\n\nRead also\n\nWilliam Ruto promises to concede defeat in 2027 General Election if he loses: \"Nitaenda kulima\"\n\nHowever, the head of state has been met with huge and eager crowds in every county he\'s visited.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nDespite the relative success, Ruto has been forced to contend with isolated incidents of hostility, mainly directed at leaders in his entourage.\n\nAt the early stages, his visit to Embu county was building up to be a feisty affair as the last time he was in the county, he received a cold welcome.\n\nOn Friday, April 4, the head of state was welcomed by jubilant crowds who lined up along the roads to welcome him.\n\nThe head of state initially had a rough time as he greeted the crowd, as a section kept shouting at him with chants of \"Uongo\"\n\nRead also\n\nWilliam Ruto forced to stop his speech as Makuyu residents start singing warning song to Gachagua\n\nThe president dismissed the chants against him before he continued with his speech, highlighting his plan to have homes in the area connected with electricity.\n\nAhead of Ruto\'s visit to Nyeri Town and Othaya constituencies on Saturday, April 5, local leaders have urged residents to show restraint and avoid heckling politicians during presidential events.\n\nThis call came after a series of confrontational incidents earlier in the week, where leaders aligned with the Kenya Kwanza coalition were publicly shouted down by residents during Ruto\'s stopovers in Nyandarua county.\n\nNyeri governor Mutahi Kahiga, addressing residents at various forums, warned that such behavior could tarnish the region\'s image and harm its standing in national development politics.\n\nRead also\n\nNyandarua woman rep defies hecklers, moves forward to address William Ruto: \"Usiskie hiyo noise\"\n\nKahiga, who has recently expressed concerns about the direction of Kenya Kwanza\'s leadership, emphasised the importance of respecting the presidency despite any internal political disagreements.\n\nThe appeal for calm follows an embarrassing incident in Nyandarua county Ruto\'s allies from the region were jeered by angry crowds while the president observed.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nDidacus Malowa (Political and current affairs editor) Didacus Malowa is a political and current affairs editor at TUKO.co.ke. He holds a Bachelor\'s Degree in Communication and Media Technology with IT from Maseno University in 2021. He has over two years of experience in digital journalism. Email: didacus.malowa@tuko.co.ke\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 19:57:49','2025-04-05 19:57:49',NULL),(45,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/entertainment/584709-mzungu-man-viral-eating-ugali-chapati-dances-matopare-dont/','Mzungu Man Goes Viral after Eating Ugali with Chapati, Dances to Matopare: “We Don’t Do That”','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nA mzungu man who seems to love the Kenyan culture has gone viral over his antics on TikTok.\n\nThe TikToker, who goes by Fresh Mzungu on the app, left many in stitches after sharing a video of himself eating Ugali with chapati.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nIf that was not enough, the man was eating with a fork and knife as he demonstrated what it is like for a foreigner on his first day in Kenya.\n\nHis facial expression showed how much he was not enjoying the meal and required some water to avoid choking.\n\nRead also\n\nBaba Jimmy moves wife, kids to safe shelter after receiving tornado warning\n\nHe then switched it up to Ugali, avocado and miraa and served himself a famous alcoholic drink in Kenya, as he also showed off his Matopare moves.\n\nHe showed great understanding of the dance style, and his cap moved exactly as it would have been with a seasoned dancer.\n\nThis was to showcase the changes that had taken place after a foreigner had spent 60 days in Kenya.\n\nThe video went viral with over 3.8 million views, 218,000 likes and 5,000 plus comments, showing how much he has gained popularity in the country.\n\nHere are some of the comments from those who watched the clip:\n\nMJ said:\n\nDiva Queen said:\n\nWinnie Kamau/ Wink Fashions said:\n\nRead also\n\nLand Cruiser with notice about accepting gently used baby mamas cracks up Kenyans\n\nking 01 said:\n\nmacmillanmasinza1 said:\n\nM.i.s.t.a.h Njenga said:\n\njymo kama@415 said:\n\nearn_online said:\n\nTEA BAG. said:\n\nPreviously, TUKO.co.ke reported on a video that went viral, showing a mzungu kid who was spotted eating ugali and meat stew.\n\nThe kid joined some Mjengo men during lunch, and his skills while eating the meal impressed many online.\n\nHe tried to pinch the huge ugali from a plate, but it seemed too hot for him, and he failed to manage.\n\nRead also\n\nKenyan doctor shattered as he picks, buries body of brother who lost cash in Aviator gambling\n\nOne of the mjengo men then handed him a small piece that had cooled down, and he was spotted dipping it in the meat stew, which excited netizens.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nVictor Otengo (Entertainment editor) Victor Otengo is the Special Projects Lead and Editor at TUKO.co.ke. He attended the Multimedia University of Kenya, where he studied for a Bachelor\'s Degree in Journalism and Mass Communication. He has seven years of experience in journalism and has previously worked as a writer at Standard Digital, reporter and sports pundit at Kwese TV (under African Insights). Email: victor.otengo@tuko.co.ke.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 19:58:02','2025-04-05 19:58:02',NULL),(46,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/219311-sonkos-secret-love-life-revealed.html','Mike Sonko\'s history with women and children sired','2017-10-16 00:00:00','Tuko','- Nairobi Senator Mike Sonko over the weekend caused a stir after declaring himself the acting President\n\n- He is, however, not new to controversy and his life with different women is quite an interesting one\n\nNairobi Senator Mike Sonko has three known children, Saumu Mbuvi, Sandra and Salma, all born of different women.\n\nREAD ALSO: Police ordered to investigate Mike Sonko over remarks\n\nThe eldest, Saumu, who recently graduated from JKUAT, was born during Sonko\'s first marriage with his late wife Njeri Wangui.\n\nThe Senator then sired another daughter, Salma with an unidentified woman who is also deceased and was celebrated by Salma on December 1, 2015 on her Instagram page.\n\nSandra, on the other hand, was born in Sonko\'s current marriage to Primrose, a wife he has introduced openly to the public.\n\nREAD ALSO: Mike Sonko declares himself president of Kenya\n\nThis is no it yet, Senator Sonko admitted early in the year to having two wives when a supporter challenged him on Facebook regarding a \'Mpango wa Kando\' situation.\n\n“I only have 2 and each has her own house and I respect them a lot especially mama watoto,” he posted.\n\nA couple of months later, photos of Sonko carrying a new-born baby while flanked by a woman emerged on social media. A weekly publication reported that the flamboyant Senator was in a secret relationship with the pictured woman since 2011.\n\nThe lady said to own a house built by the philanthropic senator was also reported to be a daughter to a serving politician from Central Kenya and had been introduced to close friends as the second wife.\n\nREAD ALSO: See Mike Sonko\'s secret wife and child\n\nSonko refuted reports that he had a secret wife and even threatened to sue the publication that first carried the story.\n\nHis drama with women does not end there. In 2014, Sonko was taken to court by a certain Josephine Thuku who wanted child support from the politician.\n\nThe Senator admitted that he was the father of her first born son but distanced himself from the second born child.\n\nHe, however, agreed to supporting Thuku\'s second child on humanitarian grounds.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nMuyela Roberto (HOD Business) Muyela Roberto is a journalist with over 9 years of experience in digital media. He graduated from Maseno University with a BA in Communication & Media with IT in 2017. He\'s the head of the business desk. He previously served as copy editor. Before copy editing, he was a business and current affairs editor. He\'s undergone training from Google News Initiative, Digital ABC by WAN-IFRA, & Media Lab 101 by Kenya Airways. Before TUKO, he worked as People Daily correspondent in Kisumu, Scholar Media correspondent and contributor at Kenya News Agency. Email: roberto.muyela@tuko.co.ke','News','2025-04-05 19:58:13','2025-04-05 19:58:13',NULL),(47,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/sports/football/584755-man-united-man-city-gary-neville-jamie-carragher-predict-manchester-derby/','Man United vs Man City: Gary Neville and Jamie Carragher Predict Manchester Derby','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: How to Start Earning with Copywriting in Just 7 Days – Even if You’re a Complete Beginner\n\nGary Neville and Jamie Carragher have predicted the Manchester derby between Manchester United and Manchester City on Sunday.\n\nSunday\'s Manchester derby, which pits the city\'s two big clubs against each other, is unlikely to bring the same hype as in previous games due to both teams\' disappointing 2024/25 campaigns.\n\nMan City have struggled to defend their Premier League title, while Man United have hovered above the relegation zone for the majority of the season.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nPep Guardiola\'s side are still fighting for a Champions League spot. They are fifth in the Premier League with eight games to go.\n\nRead also\n\nRuben Amorim jokingly trolls Kevin De Bruyne ahead of Man United vs Man City\n\nMeanwhile, Ruben Amorim\'s team are 13th with 37 points. The Red Devils are heading for their worst season in the Premier League era.\n\nNeville and Carragher expect Sunday\'s derby to end in a draw.\n\nMan United defeated Man City 2-1 in the first leg thanks to an incredible performance from Amad Diallo.\n\nAmorim has defeated the Spaniard twice this season. He led Sporting CP to an emphatic 4-1 win over the English champions in the Champions League and then his win as Man United boss in December in the Premier League.\n\nRead also\n\nWhat Neymar, Mahrez, Guardiola said about Kevin De Bruyne ahead of Man City exit\n\nGuardiola has won the last four league titles, a record in the Premier League era. He made a brief comment about Sunday\'s showdown.\n\nKevin De Bruyne\'s announcement dominated the headlines on Friday. The 33-year-old will leave the club at the end of the season and will play his final Manchester derby.\n\nTUKO.co.ke earlier reported that Amorim sent a congratulatory message to Kevin De Bruyne after his exit announcement.\n\nThe Portuguese included a cheeky dig in his brief message for the legendary midfielder.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nEdwin Kiplagat (Sports Editor) Edwin Kiplagat has 8 years of experience in journalism and is currently a sports editor at Tuko. He has written sports stories from across the African continent while at Africa InSight, ESPN, Editec, and Sports Brief. Edwin obtained a degree in Journalism from Multimedia University in 2016. Email: edwin.kiplagat@sportsbrief.com.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 19:58:23','2025-04-05 19:58:23',NULL),(48,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/entertainment/584750-siaya-woman-asked-jalango-send-ksh-1k-hubby-confirms-gave-money/','Siaya Woman Who Asked Jalang\'o to Send KSh 1k to Hubby Confirms He Gave Her Money','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','PAY ATTENTION: Flexible Payment Plans Available! Invest in Yourself & See the Return with Our Affordable Copywriting Course!\n\nSiaya woman who recently sold bananas to Langata MP Felix Odiwuor alias Jalang\'o has shared that her hubby gave her the money he sent.\n\nJalang\'o had bought bananas from the businesswoman and while paying for them, she said that she uses her husband\'s phone number for transactions.\n\nShe added that her husband was at home and that she had no problems with him being the recipient of the money.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThe Siaya returned to see Jalang\'o who engaged her further about how life had changed since she went viral.\n\nRead also\n\nNick Mudimba’s fiancée emotional while honouring journalist\n\nShe also read out her husband\'s number for those who may want to support her business with a financial boost.\n\nRead also\n\nHannah Benta addresses claims she paid for Dubai trip with Captain Sammir\n\nWatch the video below:\n\nHere are some of the reactions from social media users:\n\n@ⒷⒺⓉⒽ said:\n\n@Moyahabo Manthata said:\n\n@Tap press Inc. said\"\n\n@zamuu said:\n\n@jijo said:\n\n@Reds9539 said:\n\n@slae slae said:\n\n@henriphiri said:\n\n@M.M.Levis said:\n\nIn a different report, a woman identified as Jag Zangel sparked mixed reactions after narrating that she gave her husband almost all her salary.\n\nRead also\n\nKareh B discloses ex cheated on her with cousin in her house: \"In my bed\"\n\nJag revealed that she was trying to support him to offset some of the family\'s bills and asked couples to support each other.\n\nAccording to her, she asked her spouse how much he would need from her to cover some bills and he was baffled when she gave him the amount.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nAmondi Aroko (Entertainment editor) Amondi Aroko is an Entertainment Editor with seven years of experience in local and international media. She has worked at Family Media (Kenya), written for News Deeply, New York (USA) and done Africa news analysis on Arise News (Nigeria). Won the 2015 Local Heroes Journalism award by Deutsche Welle. Google News Initiative 2024 trainee and 2024 WAN-IFRA Media Leadership Accelerator Programme winner. Speaker at Code For Africa -media lab, and China trip attendee by CMG. Email: prisca.aroko@tuko.co.ke.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 19:58:33','2025-04-05 19:58:33',NULL),(49,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/people/relationships/584673-bomet-murder-suspect-rachealine-ruttos-killing-nabbed/','Rachealine Rutto: Murder Suspect Arrested in Brutal Killing of 45-Year-Old Bomet Woman','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: You’re One Course Away from Transforming Your Life. Learn Copywriting and Turn Your Passion into Profit\n\nBomet Central detectives have arrested the prime suspect in the brutal murder of 45-year-old Rachealine Rutto, whose lifeless body was discovered on March 25, 2025.\n\nThe grim discovery was made by the deceased’s daughter, who had grown increasingly anxious after her mother failed to answer repeated phone calls throughout the day.\n\nDriven by concern, she visited the residence, only to be met with a horrifying sight—her mother lying lifeless on the bed in a pool of blood.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThe body bore deep neck wounds and multiple stab injuries to the arm, chest, and back.\n\nRead also\n\nSylvia Kemunto: Main suspect in student\'s murder surrenders to police\n\nDetermined to bring the perpetrator to justice, detectives launched an intensive investigation.\n\nFollowing forensic leads, they tracked down 28-year-old Wesley Cheruiyot Koech, who was found hiding in Sailo village, Kipkelion East Sub-County. He was promptly arrested.\n\nDuring interrogation, Cheruiyot led detectives to his residence, where several incriminating pieces of evidence were recovered.\n\nAmong them was a bloodstained knife, suspected to be the murder weapon, wrapped in a cloth.\n\nAdditionally, police found Rutto’s ring and a mobile phone containing disturbing photographs of the victim taken by the suspect after the killing.\n\nInvestigations revealed that the motive behind the heinous act stemmed from a long-standing grudge.\n\nCheruiyot allegedly harbored resentment towards Rutto after she ended their romantic relationship in 2016 and moved on with another man.\n\nReports indicate that he felt betrayed after spending money on her during their time together.\n\nRead also\n\nKisumu: Mother arrested for scalding son with boiling water for allegedly stealing 2kg of maize\n\nThe suspect is currently in police custody, undergoing processing ahead of his court appearance.\n\nKenyans expressed fury at the murder suspect, with many questioning why a 28-year-old was in a romantic relationship with a 45-year-old.\n\nSirfred Mcauma\n\nAlphaz Njenga\n\nSimon Kamau\n\nIn another case of love gone sour, Naomi Chebet was murdered in her rental apartment in Kabete, Kiambu County.\n\nRead also\n\nVihiga man returns from work to find wife allegedly killed their 2 kids: \"Hatukukosana\"\n\nA post-mortem examination revealed that the mother of three had been stabbed twice at the back of her head.\n\nChebet\'s long-term boyfriend, Samuel Njoroge, who is the prime suspect, disappeared after sharing a disturbing message online.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nHillary Lisimba (Human-Interest editor) Hillary Lisimba Ambani is a responsive journalist who creates content that touches lives. After graduating from the University of Nairobi’s School of Journalism, he worked in Print, Broadcast, and Online media. He is a published author, former KBC producer, and former Daily Nation columnist. He is currently a human-interest editor and philanthropist. Media Council of Kenya Member No: MCK019108. Share your Human Interest stories with him at hillary.lisimba@tuko.co.ke. or find him on Facebook.','News','2025-04-05 19:58:43','2025-04-05 19:58:43',NULL),(50,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/kenya/counties/584756-14-mugoiri-girls-students-confirmed-safe-scary-accident-glory-god/','14 Mugoiri Girls Students Confirmed Safe after Scary Accident: \"Glory to God\"','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nFaith Chandianya, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over three years of experience covering politics and Current Affairs in Kenya\n\nKiambu: A scare unfolded on Friday, April 4, when a matatu carrying 14 students from Mugoiri Girls was involved in an accident in Witeithie.\n\nVideos and images seen by TUKO.co.ke showed the vehicle tipped on its side, with students and local residents gathered around the scene.\n\nIn a statement from Mugoiri Girls High School alumnae chairperson Victoria Kamau, the school principal, Susan Mundia, said the matatu operated by Muna Sacco was carrying Form Four students for the April holidays when it was allegedly forced into a drainage ditch by a bus.\n\nRead also\n\nNakuru: Mash Poa passengers injured, stranded after Nakuru-Eldoret accident\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nShe also confirmed that all 14 students involved in the accident are in good condition, with no injuries or fatalities reported.\n\nVictoria added that since the students were unharmed, they were transferred to another vehicle and allowed to continue their journey home.\n\nIn a related story, the Mbita Boys High School community was left devastated after four students were struck by a speeding vehicle.\n\nThe students were on their way home for the April holiday when the tragedy occurred.\n\nRead also\n\nDCI summons Gathoni Wamuchomba after viral \'Ruto must go\' chants video\n\nThey were reportedly negotiating the boda fare with a rider beside the road when the tragic accident occurred.\n\nOnlookers said the vehicle responsible for the accident was traveling at high speed. They also suspected that the driver was intoxicated at the time of the crash.\n\nAccording to a statement from Mbita Boys High School, the injured students were rushed to Prince Richard Hospital and Mbita Level 4 Hospital.\n\nThe administration added that two students who sustained serious injuries were referred to Homa Bay Teaching and Referral Hospital for advanced medical care.\n\nThe accident occurred shortly after three pupils from Ober Boys Primary School were killed in a crash in Nyakach Subcounty.\n\nThe fatal accident on Wednesday morning, April 2, occurred at Kibwon along the Sondu-Katito Road.\n\nIt involved a Public Service matatu ferrying pupils home for the April holidays and a lorry transporting sugarcane.\n\nAccording to the police report, four people, including three pupils, died at the scene, while nine others sustained various injuries.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nFaith Chandianya (CA editor) Faith Chandianya is a multi-media journalist and a Current Affairs Editor at TUKO.co.ke. In 2023, she graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Media Science from Moi University. She has over four years experience in digital journalism. Email: Faith.Chandianya@tuko.co.ke\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 19:59:05','2025-04-05 19:59:05',NULL),(51,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/entertainment/celebrities/584766-exclusive-lenny-speaks-githurai-hit-song-heartbreak-dads-loss/','Exclusive: Mr Lenny Speaks on Githurai Hit Song, Heartbreak after Dad’s Loss','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nWhen you mention song\'s like Githurai, Cash Money, Juju and Leo, one thing stands out, the amazing voice of one of Kenya\'s greatest ever singer Kenya has produced.\n\nHis longevity in the game is undisputed as he continues to perform to this day and his music transcends through all generations.\n\nAs he turned a year older TUKO.co.ke held an exclusive interview with the star to learn about the past and present in his personal life, music and health.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nBuckle up for this interesting chat with one of Kenya\'s top stars.\n\nRead also\n\n50+ best bar jokes and one-liners that are so hilarious\n\nI can\'t attribute it to one aspect but when we started in the early 2000s there was a gap for new music. We listened to music our fathers played and also on radio. I remember we used to watch Music Time, I think Fred Machoka used to host the show so there was music from Nigeria, South Africa, Congo, Cameron and Senega. As we grew a lot of music was from the West, soul music, rap and R&B. So a lot of music at that time was vernacular music. My dad used to listen to country music, he would play artistes like Kenny Rogers, Dolly Parton, at times Bob Marley, so you can see the bled. But there was a gap, so by the time I was clearing school there was a need for a sound we could relate to. That is how when we joined studios like Calif Records, Ogopa Dejays, Samawati etc. By the time I was joining Ogopa, we had started getting vibes from different producers and people like akina Kalamashaka, Bambo, Abass Kubaff and then akina Wyre, Nazizi joined in and they were very young artistes. We started identifying with them because they were young and had different vibe. That is how we started to emulate those that came before us and the blend of music we had listened to, we to now blend it all and created our own sound. So these styles like Kapuka and Genge came about.\n\nRead also\n\n50+ inspirational Jay-Z quotes about money, loyalty, business and hustling\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nVictor Otengo (Entertainment editor) Victor Otengo is the Special Projects Lead and Editor at TUKO.co.ke. He attended the Multimedia University of Kenya, where he studied for a Bachelor\'s Degree in Journalism and Mass Communication. He has seven years of experience in journalism and has previously worked as a writer at Standard Digital, reporter and sports pundit at Kwese TV (under African Insights). Email: victor.otengo@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 19:59:15','2025-04-05 19:59:15',NULL),(52,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/entertainment/celebrities/584725-pastor-nganga-lectures-woman-hairstyle-disclosing-hubby-dumped-her/','Pastor Ng\'ang\'a Lectures Woman Over Hairstyle after Disclosing Hubby Dumped Her','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Education is Your Right! Don’t Let Social Norms Hold You Back. Learn Online with TUKO. Enroll Now!\n\nRenowned preacher Pastor James Ng\'ang\'a has left netizens in stitches after his encounter with one of his church members.\n\nWhile preaching, a female congregant went to the altar to ask the preacher why her husband left her but his response got her thinking deep.\n\nIn the clip shared on TikTok by @grandson, the lady dressed in an orange top, had her hair shaved in a box style, and dyed the front part, which is common to men.\n\nRead also\n\nPastor Ng\'ang\'a tells off woman lamenting about hubby leaving her: \"Ni hii nywele”\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nShe said:\n\nNg\'ang\'a who was standing next to her looked at her and then said:\n\nNg\'ang\'a could be seen pointing at the woman\'s head and pushing her while asking her why she considered the short hairstyle.\n\nWatch the video below:\n\nHere are some of the reactions from social media users:\n\n@Claire said:\n\n@CATHY✨said\"\n\n@Lilly? said:\n\n@THEE__ALI?? said:\n\n@Verah Njenga said:\n\n@JOLENE__PIXIE said:\n\n@Mr.Imani Omoto said:\n\n@Kili.ke said:\n\nRead also\n\nCaptain Sammir introduces new lover hours after splitting with Sabrina\n\n@Super rider said:\n\n@Dee said:\n\nThe man of God rebuked his congregants after they failed to give hefty offerings during the church service.\n\nThe Neno Evangelism Church founder stated what he expects from them every Sunday, sparking reactions from Kenyans.\n\nAccording to him, his church members did so little for his ministry with their low attendance and few offerings.\n\nThe controversial pastor also questioned why young people in his church were struggling to attend service yet he attends overnight prayers and shows up on Sunday.\n\nThe preacher banned speaking Sheng (an English-Swahili-based chant) in his church, saying it was a language used by crooks.\n\nDuring a service in the church, he cautioned his congregants saying they ought to be civil and communicate in decent language.\n\nHe claimed that the language was rubbish and wouldn\'t be tolerated in his church as he advised them to communicate in ways everyone could understand.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nAmondi Aroko (Entertainment editor) Amondi Aroko is an Entertainment Editor with seven years of experience in local and international media. She has worked at Family Media (Kenya), written for News Deeply, New York (USA) and done Africa news analysis on Arise News (Nigeria). Won the 2015 Local Heroes Journalism award by Deutsche Welle. Google News Initiative 2024 trainee and 2024 WAN-IFRA Media Leadership Accelerator Programme winner. Speaker at Code For Africa -media lab, and China trip attendee by CMG. Email: prisca.aroko@tuko.co.ke.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 19:59:25','2025-04-05 19:59:25',NULL),(53,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/politics/584292-ruto-vows-deliver-mt-kenya-remembers-support/','Ruto Vows to Deliver for Mt Kenya, Says He Remembers Their Support: \"Mimi Si Wazimu Nisahau\"','2002-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: Don\'t let unemployment hold you back. Start your digital marketing journey today.\n\nTUKO.co.ke journalist Ivan Mboto has over three years of experience reporting on politics and current affairs in Kenya\n\nPresident William Ruto kicked off his development tour of the Mt. Kenya region, making stops in Laikipia and Nyeri counties to launch infrastructure projects.\n\nAddressing a gathering in Nyeri, Ruto fondly recalled the overwhelming support he received from the region during the 2022 General Election. He assured the residents that he had not forgotten their contribution to his presidency and that their interests remain a priority.\n\nRead also\n\nMutahi Kahiga warmly welcomes Ruto to Nyeri, urges him to return: \"Tuletee maendeleo\"\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThe president emphasised that he personally oversees the region’s development to ensure that key projects are implemented as promised.\n\nIn what seemed to be a veiled response to his former deputy Rigathi Gachagua over claims that he had sidelined the region, Ruto warned residents against falling for divisive politics.\n\nThe head of state further reassured Nyeri residents that his administration remains closely connected to the region and going forward, he would visit the region more frequently.\n\nRead also\n\nWilliam Ruto claims Rigathi Gachagua demanded KSh 10b: “I said I’ll not do it”\n\nDuring his visit to Nyeri, Ruto launched several projects aimed at improving infrastructure and living standards in the county. He flagged off the Last Mile connectivity programme worth KSh 850 million, which is set to connect 10,000 households to electricity.\n\nAdditionally, he inaugurated a newly constructed one-storey, 12-classroom tuition block at Narumoru Township Primary School and assessed the ongoing development of the Narumoru market, which is expected to be completed within a month.\n\nIn Laikipia county, the president laid the foundation for the construction of 10 new classrooms at Nanyuki DEB Primary and Junior Secondary School. He also inspected the KSh 350 million Nanyuki modern market and toured the Nanyuki affordable housing project.\n\nFurther, Ruto flagged off another phase of the Last Mile connectivity programme in Ng’arachi, pledging a KSh 1.12 billion investment to connect over 9,000 households to electricity in Laikipia.\n\nRead also\n\nWilliam Ruto maintains he\'s still popular in Mt Kenya, tells off naysayers: \"Urafiki wa miaka 20\"\n\nTo support local education and economic activities, he also handed over a school bus to Dr. Wachira Secondary School in Kiamariga and delivered car wash machines to boda boda operators in the county.\n\nNyeri Governor Mutahi Kahiga, a close ally of former deputy president Gachagua, warmly received Ruto in Kieni, praising his allocation of over KSh 850 million for local projects.\n\nHe noted the region has long suffered from underdevelopment and needs urgent investment. Kahiga highlighted funding challenges in road construction and lauded Ruto for upgrading Naromoru Hospital.\n\nReaffirming his support for Ruto, Kahiga dismissed claims the president was unwelcome in Nyeri. He urged him to visit frequently and continue implementing development projects.\n\nProofreading by Mercy Nyambura, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nHarry Ivan Mboto (Current affairs editor) Harry Ivan Mboto is an accredited journalist with the Media Council of Kenya (MCK) and a Current Affairs and Politics Editor at TUKO. He is a Linguistics, Media, and Communication student at Moi University and has over three years of experience in digital journalism. Have a news tip, query, or feedback? Reach him at: harry.ivan@tuko.co.ke.\n\nMercy Nyambura (Copyeditor)','News','2025-04-05 19:59:37','2025-04-05 19:59:37',NULL),(54,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/people/584681-mike-sonko-vows-machakos-woman-attacked-by-hyenas-tsavo-nitakulipia-nyumba-3-months/','Mike Sonko Vows to Help Machakos Woman Attacked by Hyenas in Tsavo: \"Nitakulipia Nyumba 3 Months\"','2004-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: How to Secure Copywriting Gigs Fast – So You Can Turn Words Into Money Right Now\n\nFormer Nairobi governor Mike Mbuvi Sonko has expressed his compassion by coming through for a desperate woman.\n\nThe philanthropist came through for Irene Mbithe Wambua, a lady who was attacked by hyenas in Tsavo West National Park.\n\nShe consequently lost an arm and eye, which were removed to avoid being paralysed after the gruesome attack.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nDuring a live interview, the woman received a call from Sonko, who was touched by her heartbreaking story.\n\nRead also\n\nSiaya woman who asked Jalang\'o to send KSh 1k to hubby confirms he gave her money\n\nMbithe was emotional after the politician reached out to her and promised to change her life for the better.\n\nShe noted she was afraid she would never see again, as her right eye, which remained intact, was having issues.\n\nHowever, her hopes were revived with the potentially life-changing call from Sonko, who has helped several individuals.\n\nIn a follow-up call with Mbithe, she told TUKO.co.ke she was delighted to receive massive help from Sonko.\n\nRead also\n\nKakamega: Married man nursing injuries after being bitten by side chick\n\nSonko\'s response to the woman\'s cry was welcomed warmly as Kenyans lauded him for his kindness and thoughtful gesture.\n\nrachelwaweru1309:\n\nKIBEKAVENGI:\n\nalfanmwatamu9030L:\n\nalexsaidi3940:\n\nRead also\n\nMike Sonko gets piggy bank for son James, helps him start saving: \"Mapema ndio best\"\n\nsurandre1055:\n\nwashingtonochanda4527\n\nIn another story, Sonko came to the rescue of former Citizen TV journalist Kimani Mbugua following his relapse.\n\nMbugua was found loitering in Thika and was immediately taken to Sonko\'s headquarters for care.\n\nKindhearted Sonko gave him new clothes, offered him a meal and arranged for him to be taken to a rehabilitation centre in Mombasa.\n\nProofreading by Mercy Nyambura, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nRacheal Nyaguthie (HOD Human interest) Racheal Nyaguthie is an accredited journalist in Kenya and is currently the Head of the Human Interest Department at TUKO. She has five years of experience in digital journalism, having previously worked in Tuko\'s Current Affairs desk as a senior politics and current Affairs editor. Racheal was also a recipient of the AWiM Women in Politics Fellowship programme, where she investigated the experiences of Kenyan women in politics. She is also passionate about Environmental and SRHR reporting. Email: racheal.nyaguthie@tuko.co.ke.\n\nMercy Nyambura (Copyeditor)','News','2025-04-05 20:00:14','2025-04-05 20:00:14',NULL),(55,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/politics/584752-dci-summons-gathoni-wamuchomba-viral-ruto-chants-video/','DCI Summons Gathoni Wamuchomba after Viral \'Ruto Must Go\' Chants Video','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: How to Secure Copywriting Gigs Fast – So You Can Turn Words Into Money Right Now\n\nFaith Chandianya, a journalist at TUKO.co.ke, brings over three years of experience covering politics and Current Affairs in Kenya\n\nThe Directorate of Criminal Investigations has summoned Githunguri MP Gathoni Wamuchomba over alleged incitement of a crowd during President William Ruto\'s tour on Friday, April 4.\n\nThis follows a viral video showing Wamuchomba leading her constituents in chanting the \"Ruto must go\" slogan before Ruto\'s visit to their area.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nWamuchomba was seen leading a large crowd, which closely followed her while calling out the head of state.\n\nRead also\n\nMoses Wetang’ula’s daughter weds in colourful traditional wedding\n\nThe legislator, a close ally of former deputy president Rigathi Gachagua, took to her X platform to announce that she had received a phone call notifying her of the summons.\n\nAccording to Wamuchomba, she was summoned because the people of Githunguri, her area of jurisdiction, reportedly rejected false promises and projects that never materialised.\n\nThe MP also appeared to hit out at the head of state, urging him to ensure that every promise made to Kenyans is fulfilled.\n\nWamuchomba is not the first Gachagua ally to be summoned by the DCI.\n\nRead also\n\nKisumu: Mother arrested for scalding son with boiling water for allegedly stealing 2kg of maize\n\nIn November 2024, Kiambu senator Karungo Thang\'wa was summoned by investigators over the chaos that erupted at a funeral in Limuru attended by Gachagua.\n\nThis followed running battles during the funeral of the late Erastus Nduati at the Bibirioni Boys High School playground, after goons infiltrated the event.\n\nA viral video showed the rowdy individuals tearing down the VIP tent where Gachagua was seated, causing him to flee for safety without addressing the mourners.\n\nAfterward, Gachagua issued a statement accusing the Kenya Kwanza government of withdrawing his security, leaving him vulnerable to the attack at the Limuru funeral.\n\nFollowing the dramatic events, the DCI began investigating the matter and summoned Senator Karungo for questioning.\n\nIn a notice issued on November 28, 2024, the investigative unit outlined that they expect the lawmaker\'s cooperation as they investigated the chaos.\n\nThe notice mentioned the destruction of property of unknown value and injuries resulting from the dramatic turn of events.\n\nRead also\n\nMurang\'a: Blow to Gachagua as Maragua MP ditches his camp, declares support for Ruto\n\nKarungo took to social media, accusing the DCI of using intimidation tactics to silence him and others opposing the government.\n\nHe also expressed frustration over being summoned in Nyeri for an incident that took place in Limuru.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nFaith Chandianya (CA editor) Faith Chandianya is a multi-media journalist and a Current Affairs Editor at TUKO.co.ke. In 2023, she graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Media Science from Moi University. She has over four years experience in digital journalism. Email: Faith.Chandianya@tuko.co.ke\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 20:00:24','2025-04-05 20:00:24',NULL),(56,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/sports/576520-who-kenny-andersons-spouse-everything-know/','Who is Kenny Anderson\'s spouse? Everything you should know','2011-02-25 00:00:00','Tuko','Kenny Anderson is a former professional basketball player. He is renowned for his skills as a point guard in a 14-year professional career, which he mostly played in the NBA. He achieved many milestones, including being named an NBA All-Star. His fame has made fans curious about his personal life. So, is he in a relationship? If so, who is Kenny Anderson\'s spouse?\n\nKenny Anderson\'s love life has always been a subject of curiosity for his fans. With a career that kept him in the spotlight, many have wondered about the relationships and romances shaping Kenny\'s journey. The star has been married thrice and divorced twice, and fans want more details about his current spouse. Who is Kenny Anderson\'s wife?\n\nRead also\n\nLeah Williamson\'s partner and her dating history explored\n\nKenny Anderson\'s wife is Natasha Anderson. The couple has been together for over 20 years, sharing their lives both in the public eye and privately. Natasha has been a strong support system for Kenny, especially during his post-basketball career transitions.\n\nNatasha Angela Anderson was born on September 5, 1980, in Greenhead, Florida, USA. She attended Florida Atlantic University and graduated with a degree in Social Work in 2004. Natasha then joined Barry University, graduating with a Master of Social Work (MSW) degree in 2009.\n\nAccording to LinkedIn, Natasha Anderson has held significant roles in healthcare and administration. She is currently a Community Medical Liaison at IQVIA for Janssen Neuroscience. Before this, she was the Chief Operating Officer at My Psychiatrist (2021–2022) and a Compliance Project Manager at Jackson Memorial Hospital (2018–2019).\n\nShe was the CEO of Larkin Behavioral Health Services (2015–2017) and the Vice President of Outpatient Behavioral Health at Larkin Community Hospital (2012–2015).\n\nRead also\n\nWho is Dom Disandro\'s wife? Everything you need to know\n\nKenny Anderson and Natasha Anderson met during the 2004 NBA playoffs. Kenny was injured for the Indiana Pacers at the time, and Natasha was a graduate student in social work.\n\nAccording to Natasha, she had gone to watch the game and was sitting courtside in the seats of her best friend\'s father. She told the story to the Washington Post in 2009:\n\nNatasha continued:\n\nRead also\n\nDid Kristen Saban divorce her husband after James Taylor affair?\n\nThe couple quickly hit it off and began dating soon after their first meeting. They eventually got married in a private ceremony in July 2007.\n\nKenny Anderson has eight children: seven biological and one stepchild. His eldest is daughter Danielle, with his first baby mother; two daughters, Jazz and Lyric, with his first wife, Tami Roman; and a son, Kenneth Jr., with his second wife, Tamiyka Lockhart.\n\nHe also has children with two other women: Kenneth Jr., Devin with Suany Castro, and daughter Christy with DJ Spinderella. The stepchild is his current wife\'s (Natasha\'s) daughter, Tiana, from a previous relationship.\n\nKenny has two ex-wives, Tami Roman, who he married from 1994 to 2001 and Tamiyka Lockhart, who he married from 2002 to 2004. Kenny Anderson\'s first ex-wife, Tami Roman, is an American television personality who first gained fame on The Real World: Los Angeles in 1993.\n\nRead also\n\nWho is Justin Fields\' wife? All about the quarterback\'s love life\n\nRead also\n\nMeet JJ Redick\'s wife, Chelsea Kilgore, and their sons Kai and Knox\n\nKenny Anderson\'s spouse, Natasha Anderson, is a healthcare professional from Florida. She has been married to Kenny since 2007, and together, they raise two children: Kenny Jr. and Tiana from Natasha\'s previous relationship. Despite being married to a famous personality, Natasha prefers a private life, hence public interest in her life.\n\nAre you looking for information about Larry Bird\'s wife? Tuko.co.ke published an informative article detailing his wife, Dinah Mattingly\'s life.\n\nLarry Bird and Dinah Mattingly have been together for a long time. Their enduring relationship has generated interest from the public, who want to know more about them. Read the article to learn more about Larry Bird\'s wife.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nSimon Ayub (Lifestyle writer) Simon Ayub is a Content Manager, Strategist, and writer who joined Tuko\'s team in 2019. He graduated in 2014 with a BSc in Agricultural Economics and is a CPA. Simon has over a decade of experience creating content for nyagah.co.ke, the Hoth and other platforms. He works on content encompassing biographies, fashion and lifestyle, gaming, and more. Simon was awarded the \"Writer of the Year\" 2024 on Tuko. In 2023, Simon finished the AFP course on Digital Investigation Techniques and, in 2024, expanded their skills through the Google Initiative Course. You can reach him via simonayub@gmail.com.','News','2025-04-05 20:00:33','2025-04-05 20:00:33',NULL),(57,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/sports/562899-list-fastest-growing-sports-world-watch/','List of fastest growing sports in the world to watch out for in 2025','2012-03-25 00:00:00','Tuko','The global sports landscape continues evolving as new sports emerge and capture the audience\'s attention. Beyond that, multiple sports are poised to experience exponential growth due to increased fan engagement and media coverage. With that in mind, which are the fastest-growing sports in the world?\n\nThis list of the fastest-growing sports in the world was curated using data from Charlotte’s Web, University Magazine, and TalentBacker. Our analysis is based on several factors, including accessibility, global appeal, and market value. So, which are the up-and-coming sports in the world?\n\nThere are plenty of sports people can take part in. Nonetheless, more activities are gaining popularity due to social and community appeal, health and fitness trends, and media and digital coverage. Here are the new popular sports.\n\nRead also\n\nTara Strong\'s net worth makes her one of the highest-paid voice actors\n\nMixed martial arts has an estimated global audience of 451 million fans. The largest audience share is outside the United States, with Brazil being the fastest-growing market, adding about 8 million fans. This boards well for revenue generation.\n\nAs of 2023, the Ultimate Fighting Championship (UFC), the biggest MMA promoter, had topped $700 million in revenue. Moreover, its popularity is sustained by mega fighters like Conor McGregor and Ronda Rousey. Additionally, social media is fueling its growth among younger audiences.\n\nOver 320 million people watched the Drone Racing League (DRL) in 2022/23, indicating a growing audience. The industry is financially lucrative, with a projected worth of over $2,238.1 million by 2033. Additionally, investments in drone companies reached about $1.54 billion in 2022.\n\nRead also\n\nWho owns Zeus Network now? Everything you should know\n\nAn estimated 300 million people play table tennis worldwide. The sport is primarily popular in China but is now the fastest-growing sport in America. Its growth is driven by its ability to play indoors, ease of play, and sociability. Regarding its marketability, the sport’s revenue is estimated to reach $242 million in 2024 and US$432.8 million by 2032.\n\nEsports has gained prominence over the last few years, becoming one of the fastest-growing sports in the world. There are over 285.7 million esports enthusiasts worldwide, compared to 234 million in 2021 and 197 million in 2019.\n\nRead also\n\nCaseOh\'s net worth and earnings: What does he do for a living?\n\nFurthermore, the esports industry\'s revenue was valued at $1.6 billion in 2023 and is expected to reach $4.3 billion in 2024. Regarding the user base, the industry is expected to have 896.0 million users by 2029.\n\nThe International Federation of Sport Climbing (IFSC) shows 44.5 million climbers worldwide. This includes indoor and outdoor climbers, excluding adventure park and hikers. Climbing\'s rise in popularity is partly due to its inclusion in the Tokyo 2020 Olympics. Moreover, it can be done for fun at home or in a climbing centre.\n\nPickleball is the fastest-growing sport in the US. Its participation rate has grown to 171.1% between 2018 and 2022. A report by the Association of Pickleball Professionals released by CNBC shows that more than 36.5 million played the game between August 2021 and August 2022.\n\nRead also\n\nThe best South African series on Netflix right now (2025)\n\nThe sport is gaining exposure through sponsorships, participation by elite athletes like LeBron James and Patrick Mahomes and court accessibility. Additionally, pickleball is affordable compared to tennis and golf and is highly sociable, providing an outlet for people to make new friends.\n\nPadel is the sport with the highest growth rate in the world. The World Padel Report 2024 shows 30 million amateur sports players across 130 countries. Of these, 600,000 are registered under a federation.\n\nPadel’s growth is fueled by its simplicity, which encourages beginners to try it. It can also be played in doubles, promoting social interaction. Padel is primarily played in Europe, which also has the highest number of courts, 42,600.\n\nRead also\n\nHighest paid female soccer players in the world in 2025\n\nWomen’s football is among the two most valuable elite women’s sports, with Deloitte projecting it will generate about $555 million by 2024.\n\nIts biggest tournament, the FIFA Women’s World Cup, is expected to generate significant revenue, making up 33%—or $425 million together with tennis—of the expected total revenue in women’s sports.\n\nFurthermore, broadcast deals, sponsorship, increased stadium attendance, and significant participation (29 million girls and women) are spurring this growth.\n\nRugby Sevens is the short form of rugby 15s and is much faster, shorter, and more thrilling. It gained popularity after being included in Brazil\'s 2016 Summer Olympic Games. The sport attracts over 8.46 million participants globally, including 1.5 million active non-registered, 1.9 active registered, and 5 million registered players.\n\nRead also\n\nMost profitable sports leagues in the world (with revenues)\n\nFormula One’s global appeal is rising due to its Netflix series “Drive to Survive.” Over 400 thousand people watched season four, compared to around 200 thousand who watched season 3.\n\nAt the same time, the American audience will reach 49.2 million in 2024 from 44.9 million in 2019. On top of that, around 1.5 billion fans globally watched races on television, and 5.7 million attended live races.\n\nThe fastest-growing sports in the world attract a large fanbase, lucrative sponsorship, and a large following among the population. Additionally, they are easy to play and are easily accessible.\n\nTuko.co.ke shared an article on the most dangerous sports in the world. These activities carry an inherent death or injury risk because of their modes of practice and the lack of protective equipment. Read the article to find out the grim statistics behind these sports.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nAgnes Amondi (Lifestyle and sports writer) Agnes Amondi is a journalist and sports content writer with 6 years of experience. Her sports writing journey began as an intern at Citizen Digital, Royal Media Services in Nairobi, Kenya. After graduating in 2019 with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Journalism from the United States International University-Africa (USIU-Africa), she wrote for several publications: soka25east.com, Her Football Hub, Tisini, and Spotcovery. At Tuko.co.ke, Agnes continues her sports writing endeavors by delivering insightful sports-related articles. Email: agnesamondi@gmail.com','News','2025-04-05 20:00:43','2025-04-05 20:00:43',NULL),(58,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/people/family/584754-nick-mudimbas-mum-painfully-eulogises-emotional-sendoff-ive-lost-god/','Nick Mudimba\'s Mum Painfully Eulogises Him in Emotional Sendoff: \"I\'ve Lost, God Knows Why\"','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: Why Wait for Opportunities to Come to You? Master Copywriting Today, So You Can Start Earning Tomorrow\n\nGem, Siaya: Kenyans and the family of Nick Mudimba are struggling to come to terms with the painful demise of the young man.\n\nHis mother, Mary Atieno Mudimba, tried to keep calm as she talked about her son, eulogising him with sweet words.\n\nArrayed in a white dress, Atieno stood confidently in front of the mourners as she talked about Nick at his burial in Siaya county.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nRead also\n\nNick Mudimba’s sister breaks down while eulogising brother during his burial: “I’m broken\"\n\nThe grieving mum added Nick planned to install electricity in his aunt\'s house in Kisumu county, but that remained a wish after his death.\n\nNick, who left behind an expectant wife, also planned to build a cottage house and had bought the materials, but they were lying around without purpose following the journalist\'s death.\n\nRead also\n\nBusia mum desperately appeals for justice for MKU son found dead in forest: \"Shule iwajibike\"\n\nIn another story, Lang\'ata Member of Parliament (MP) Phelix Odiwuor, alias Jalang\'o, penned an emotional tribute to the journalist.\n\nHe shared a touching tribute during Nick\'s requiem mass at the Holy Family Basilica church.\n\nJalang\'o remembered Nick for his contributions to the media industry and impact on those who knew him.\n\nThe politician who was a close friend to Nick opened up about their shared dreams and similarities.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nJohn Green (Editor of parenting content) John Green is an editor of parenting content on the Human Interest Desk. He graduated with a degree in Bachelor of Journalism from the Multimedia University of Kenya (MMU). He has also received training from Google and WAN-IFRA. He previously worked at The Exchange and SportsLeo. John joined Tuko.co.ke in 2022. Email: john.green@tuko.co.ke\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 20:00:53','2025-04-05 20:00:53',NULL),(59,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/entertainment/celebrities/584249-simon-kabu-buys-daughter-maurine-3-vehicles-worth-ksh-30-million/','Simon Kabu Buys Daughter Morine 3 Vehicles Worth KSh 30m','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: You’re One Course Away from Transforming Your Life. Learn Copywriting and Turn Your Passion into Profit\n\nBusinessman Simon Kabu has delighted netizens after buying his daughter Morine three tour vans to continue running her company.\n\nKabu and his daughter have been running their tours and travel agency after things between him and his wife went sour.\n\nThe businessman had been working closely with his estranged wife Sarah Mtalii up until late 2024 when issues about their marriage went public.\n\nIn a video that he shared on his Facebook, Kabu acknowledged his daughter\'s efforts and shared why he thought it wise to buy her the brand-new vans.\n\nRead also\n\nSiaya woman who asked Jalang\'o to send KSh 1k to hubby confirms he gave her money\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nHis daughter overwhelmed by the gifts was speechless as she thanked her dad for supporting her business.\n\nKabu further told his daughter that he was willing to give him any tools she would need to advance in her business.\n\nRead also\n\nMike Sonko\'s daughter Saumu Mbuvi shares reasons she chose to relocate to Dubai\n\nWatch the video below:\n\nHere are some of the reactions from social media users:\n\n@Jackie Koli said:\n\n@Gast Munyua Muhinga said:\n\n@Daisy Nyabs said:\n\n@Dorcas Muya said:\n\n@Catherine Njoroge said:\n\nThe businessman\'s daughter was recently awarded the Youngest Entrepreneur Award, leaving her father over the moon.\n\nRead also\n\nSimon Kabu proudly supports daughter Maurine as she wins prestigious award: \"Beyond thrilled\"\n\nShe shared a video walking to the stage to pick up her award and took a minute to note the impact her dad has had on her.\n\nNetizens congratulated her for her win and noted how she was slowly walking in her father\'s footsteps.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nAmondi Aroko (Entertainment editor) Amondi Aroko is an Entertainment Editor with seven years of experience in local and international media. She has worked at Family Media (Kenya), written for News Deeply, New York (USA) and done Africa news analysis on Arise News (Nigeria). Won the 2015 Local Heroes Journalism award by Deutsche Welle. Google News Initiative 2024 trainee and 2024 WAN-IFRA Media Leadership Accelerator Programme winner. Speaker at Code For Africa -media lab, and China trip attendee by CMG. Email: prisca.aroko@tuko.co.ke.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 20:01:02','2025-04-05 20:01:02',NULL),(60,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/business-economy/584710-kenya-import-5m-bags-yellow-maize-unga-prices-skyrocket/','Kenya to Import Over 5m Bags of Yellow Maize After Unga Prices Skyrocket','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','PAY ATTENTION: Flexible Payment Plans Available! Invest in Yourself & See the Return with Our Affordable Copywriting Course!\n\nJaphet Ruto is a journalist at TUKO.co.ke with over eight years of experience covering finance, business, and technology. He offers an in-depth analysis of economic trends in Kenya and across the region.\n\nThe government will allow the importation of 5.5 million bags of yellow maize for a year with a 50% duty waiver for importers.\n\nMutahi Kagwe, the Cabinet Secretary for Agriculture and Livestock noted animal feed millers with adequate capacity would handle the imports.\n\nRead also\n\nTrump\'s tariff Big Bang puts global economy under threat\n\nKagwe said the aim was to switch animal feed millers to yellow maize to lessen the strain on local white maize whose costs had soared by 26%.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nThe CS explained that the move would cut production costs and give consumers more consistent unga pricing by enabling millers who prioritise human consumption to acquire available maize at more affordable prices.\n\nThe cost of production has been directly impacted by the rising trend in maize prices, which has led millers to raise the price of maize flour (unga) for consumers.\n\nRead also\n\nPacific nations perplexed, worried by Trump tariffs\n\nTo meet the domestic demand of more than 1 million metric tonnes needed annually by the animal feed sector, Kagwe encouraged farmers to consider growing yellow maize in the future.\n\nHe pointed out that this will boost the economy and lessen reliance on imports.\n\nCS Kagwe said the government will release ordinary maize from the National Strategic Food Reserve to millers who manufacture unga.\n\nKenyans grappled with high unga prices in 2023, which ranged from KSh 180 to KSh 200 for a two-kilo packet.\n\nThis was made worse by high maize prices brought on by a protracted drought.\n\nThe same quantity now costs approximately KSh 150, with prices varying depending on the brands.\n\nIn related news, the Ministry of Agriculture said 7.2 million bags of subsidised fertiliser would be distributed to farmers during the 2025 long rains season which is ongoing.\n\nRead also\n\n\'Everyone worried\' by Trump tariffs in France\'s champagne region\n\nFarmers would buy the commodity at KSh 2,500 for a 50kg bag.\n\nThe government wants to make sure farmers have enough fertiliser to meet the nation\'s food production needs.\n\nIt stated that it needs KSh 20 billion to meet the country\'s requirement for 12 million bags of fertiliser.\n\nThe ministry disclosed that, of the 34 companies that applied, 13 were awarded tenders to supply fertiliser.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nJaphet Ruto (Current Affairs and Business Editor) Japhet Ruto is an award-winning TUKO.co.ke journalist with over eight years of working experience in the media industry. Ruto graduated from Moi University in 2015 with a Bachelor’s Degree in Communication and Journalism. He is a Business & Tech Editor. Ruto won the 2019 BAKE Awards’ Agriculture Blog of the Year. He was named TUKO.co.ke\'s best current affairs editor in 2020 and 2021. In 2022 and 2023, he was TUKO.co.ke\'s best business editor. He completed the Experimenting with new formats and Advance digital reporting curriculum from Google News Initiative. Email: japhet.ruto@tuko.co.ke.\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 20:01:11','2025-04-05 20:01:11',NULL),(61,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/people/family/584749-sylvia-kemuntos-heartbroken-mum-appeals-justice-mmu-daughter-nakuanga-mama-mboga/','Sylvia Kemunto\'s Heartbroken Mum Appeals for Justice for MMU Daughter: \"Nakuanga Mama Mboga\"','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: Why Wait for Opportunities to Come to You? Master Copywriting Today, So You Can Start Earning Tomorrow\n\nThe mother of the Multimedia University (MMU) student who was allegedly murdered by her lover is struggling to come to terms with her daughter\'s demise.\n\nFriends and family showed up at the house of the grieving woman, who refused to be comforted after losing her daughter, Sylvia Kemunto.\n\nFellow mourners tried to console the weeping woman who had lost a first-year university student daughter painfully.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nShe painfully opened up about her daughter\'s educational background, highlighting her academic prowess.\n\nRead also\n\nBusia mum desperately appeals for justice for MKU son found dead in forest: \"Shule iwajibike\"\n\nWith tears rolling down her sorrowful face, the downcast mother, experiencing an unimaginable pain, desperately asked for justice for her daughter.\n\nShe pleaded for true and concrete justice, noting she did not want the suspect to be caught and released until proven innocent.\n\nThe family remembered Kemunto as a jovial and hardworking girl with a dream of helping her family.\n\nA kin noted Kemunto was a cool, calm and collected young lady and was a lady of few words who loved peace.\n\nRead also\n\nSylvia Kemunto: Sorrow as Multimedia University First Year student who went missing on Sunday is found dead\n\nKemunto was allegedly killed by a man reported to be her lover after she refused his advances several times.\n\nHer heartbroken mother vividly and tearfully recounted learning of her daughter\'s death.\n\nShe had sent her some money for upkeep through a church elder\'s phone, but the Mass Communication and Computer Science student did not confirm receipt, which was unlike her.\n\nKemunto\'s mum tried to call her number but her daughter was not picking up, leaving the mother worried.\n\nShe went to the school, worrying for her daughter\'s safety, only to find out that she was missing.\n\nShe filed a missing person\'s report at Lang\'ata Police Station after the school confirmed the student\'s disappearance, which was followed by a frantic search.\n\nThe body of the student was found in a water tank on Wednesday, April 2, in an incident that left many shattered.\n\nProofreading by Asher Omondi, copy editor at TUKO.co.ke.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nJohn Green (Editor of parenting content) John Green is an editor of parenting content on the Human Interest Desk. He graduated with a degree in Bachelor of Journalism from the Multimedia University of Kenya (MMU). He has also received training from Google and WAN-IFRA. He previously worked at The Exchange and SportsLeo. John joined Tuko.co.ke in 2022. Email: john.green@tuko.co.ke\n\nAsher Omondi (Copyeditor) Asher Omondi is a political and current affairs editor with over six years of experience in digital media. Previously, he had worked in various organisations both as a social media manager and a monitor (FEMNET, Ghafla Kenya). He was a Broadcast Journalism student at the Kenya Institute of Mass Communication class of 2013. You can reach Asher at asher.omondi@tuko.co.ke.','News','2025-04-05 20:01:12','2025-04-05 20:01:12',NULL),(62,'https://www.tuko.co.ke/people/family/584748-kericho-woman-stuck-mombasa-hospital-ksh-63-million-bill/','Kericho Woman Stranded at Mombasa Hospital Over KSh 6.3 Million Bill','2005-04-25 00:00:00','Tuko','CHECK OUT: How to Start Earning with Copywriting in Just 7 Days – Even if You’re a Complete Beginner\n\nMombasa – A woman from Kericho County is stranded at Pandya Hospital in Mombasa despite being discharged.\n\nThis is because the 27-year-old is unable to clear a massive medical bill totaling KSh 6.3 million.\n\nFaith Cherono, a former student at the Technical University of Mombasa, was admitted to the hospital after falling seriously ill on January 20.\n\nPAY ATTENTION: TUKO is in WhatsApp Channels now! Subscribe and read news in favourite messenger.\n\nDisability Inclusion Champion Jonathan Metet told TUKO.co.ke that Cherono was diagnosed with motor axonal Guillain-Barré syndrome, a rare and severe neurological disorder that affects the peripheral nerves.\n\nRead also\n\nTrans Nzoia: 21-year-old woman dies during delivery amid alleged medical negligence\n\nShe was initially placed in the general ward on February 5 for four days before her condition worsened.\n\nThis led to her transfer to the Intensive Care Unit (ICU) on February 9, where she remained for a month.\n\nAlthough she has recovered enough to be discharged, her release has been delayed due to the outstanding hospital bill.\n\nTo make matters worse, she continues to accrue daily charges of approximately KSh 12,000 for staying at the facility.\n\nMetet, a National Disability Rights Advocate, visited Cherono at the hospital, where he learnt that she was discharged on March 20 but is still held at the hospital to date.\n\nHe called upon well-wishers to come to her aid.\n\nRead also\n\nMurang\'a woman stuck in hospital with late daughter\'s infant twins over KSh 183k bill\n\nA fundraiser to help settle the bill is scheduled for Saturday, April 5, at her home in Tegat Kipwastuiyo, Bureti Sub-county, Kericho County.\n\nWell-wishers are encouraged to contribute whatever they can to help secure Faith’s release.\n\nDonations can be sent via Paybill number 8061165, Account name: Faith Cherono Boit. KSh 50, 100, 200, 400, 500, 1,000, or more contributions are welcome.\n\nFor now, Faith remains hopeful that the goodwill of Kenyans will give her a chance to return home and rebuild her life.\n\nMurang\'a Woman Stuck in Hospital with Late Daughter\'s Infant Twins over KSh 183k Bill Updated Saturday, April 05, 2025 at 5:17 PM by Lynn-Linzer Kibebe reviewed by Asher Omondi 4 min read\n\nIn another plea, Ann Maina is seeking KSh 183,860 to settle a hospital bill and discharge her grandchildren from Thika Level 5 Hospital.\n\nRead also\n\nDennis Kiprotich: Autopsy sheds light on Nakuru tout’s mysterious death in police custody\n\nThis is after she was left with a pair of twins who were born prematurely and spent months in the nursery following their mother\'s demise.\n\nJudy Wambui died of complications during childbirth, and her SHA insurance was not valid to pay the bill.\n\nSource: TUKO.co.ke\n\nHillary Lisimba (Human-Interest editor) Hillary Lisimba Ambani is a responsive journalist who creates content that touches lives. After graduating from the University of Nairobi’s School of Journalism, he worked in Print, Broadcast, and Online media. He is a published author, former KBC producer, and former Daily Nation columnist. He is currently a human-interest editor and philanthropist. Media Council of Kenya Member No: MCK019108. Share your Human Interest stories with him at hillary.lisimba@tuko.co.ke. or find him on Facebook.','News','2025-04-05 20:01:21','2025-04-05 20:01:21',NULL);
